title: corn muffins*
directions: Mix milk, egg and oil.
Put dry ingredients in bowl and add liquid mix.
Stir quickly.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 425° oven.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken with bell pepper, onions and celery.
Debone cooked chicken.
Cook spaghetti or vermicelli in chicken broth. Combine chicken broth and spices with spaghetti.
Add chicken soup and mushroom soup.
Add grated cheese to this.
Mix well.
Place in baking dish.
Add cheese to top of mixture in baking dish. Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts and mixture is slightly brown.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: Pour lemon-lime soda in blender and sprinkle with gelatine. Soften for 1 minute.
Heat orange soda to boiling, add to blender and run until gelatine is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients except pineapple.
Run until smooth.
Pour into bowl and chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites; stir in pineapple.
Pour into mold and chill until set.
Whole recipe equals lunch portion of cheese and one fruit.
(Could also count towards dinner protein.)
Could use diet ginger ale in place of lemon-lime soda.

title: black bottom fruit and nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In small saucepan, melt chocolate chips and margarine over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Spread evenly over bottom of greased pan. Refrigerate until set.

title: christmas morning dish
directions: Layer croutons, ham and cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine eggs, milk, mustard, mushrooms, onion, salt and pepper in bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over layers.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: salmon balls
directions: Drain and flake salmon; remove skin and bones.
Combine salmon, cream cheese, lemon juice, horseradish and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill about 4 hours, then roll in small balls. Combine 1/4 cup chopped pecans and 3 tablespoons parsley flakes. Roll balls into nut mixture and chill well before serving.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat with spoon.
Drop batter by teaspoon into boiling water (salted) or chicken broth. After a few minutes, drain and rinse dumplings with cold water.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet with butter flavored Crisco.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on cooling rack.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: date nut pudding
directions: On top of stove, cook milk, sugar, eggs, yolks, vanilla and dates.
Add cornstarch to thicken pudding.

title: more
directions: Brown meat with onion and bell peppers in skillet; drain.
Cook 1 package of noodles in salty water; add meat to noodles.
Layer in casserole dish with corn and English peas.
Pour tomato sauce over mixture.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: oven baked chicken breasts
directions: Add salt to margarine.
Dip chicken into margarine; coat with potato chips.
Place skin side up in baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Boil 3/4 cup of water.
Mix 1/4 cup of cold water with 1/4 cup cornmeal.
Stir into boiling water and cook 10 minutes. (Microwave, if desired.)
Blend the cashews, pimientos, salt, onion powder, garlic and dill.
Add cooked mush gradually.
Add lemon juice.

title: heavenly delight dessert
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine flour, softened margarine and 1 cup pecans with pastry blender until crumbly.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan to form crust.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° and set out to cool.

title: zucchini dressing casserole
directions: Mix together. Put in a buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a ring mold sprayed with nonstick spray.
Chill until firm.

title: butterscotch wafers
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup and water in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Insert candy thermometer and cook without stirring to 265°.
Add butter (be sure not to use margarine) and continue cooking to 290°.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls onto greased (butter is best) cookie sheet (make cookies about the size of a quarter).
When cool, remove from pan and store in airtight container.

title: cartwright's coleslaw(as served at the trolley bar)
directions: Shred fine cabbage, carrot and onion.
Combine with mayonnaise (salad dressing won't work), sugar, salt and pimentos; mix well. Store in refrigerator at least 2 hours.

title: sausage cake
directions: Mix sausage, sugar and spices.
Boil raisins in water until only 1 cup of fluid remains from original 2 cups.
Add soda to 1 cup of fluid from raisins.
Add to sausage mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Add raisins, nuts and dates.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan, stir together sugar and cocoa powder.
Stir in milk.
Add butter or margarine and corn syrup.
Bring to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Boil vigorously for 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, then rolled oats.
Beat until slightly thickened. Drop from a spoon onto waxed paper.
If mixture spreads too much, beat a little longer. Cool.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer. Form into ball and put on plate. Refrigerate. Serve with your choice of crackers (Ritz crackers taste great).

title: coconut sour cream pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. In large bowl, combine butter and sugar. Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in coconut extract. In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt. Mix well. In small bowl, combine sour cream and orange juice. Blend well. Add about 1/3 of flour mixture to butter mixture. Blend well. Add about half of sour cream mixture. Blend well. Repeat with half of flour mixture, remaining sour cream and remaining flour. Stir in coconut. Pour batter into tube pan that has been greased. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove from pan to wire rack.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Arrange in layers.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake in slow oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cover chicken with water in large roasting pan.
Season with salt, pepper and 2 bouillon cubes for every cup of water used to cover chicken.
Bake in oven at 400° for 3 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken from broth; cool and bone out.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Combine mayonnaise, pickles, salt, black pepper and sugar in a bowl.
Shell eggs; cut in halves.
Spoon out and combine yellow yolks with mixture in bowl.
Stir until completely smooth.
Spoon mixture into halved eggs.
Let chill for a half hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix salmon, milk and crumbs; add beaten eggs.
Add onion, parsley, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Pack in greased loaf pan; bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Bless my little kitchen, Lord

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat the cream cheese and sugar until blended.
Add fruit; fold in Cool Whip.
Mix together and freeze.
Will serve 6 or 8.

title: pluck it coffee cake
directions: Quarter biscuits.
Place half of the biscuits in well-greased Bundt pan.
Mix other ingredients; pour half mixture over biscuits.
Put other half of the biscuits in pan.
Pour remainder of mixture over top.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool before cutting in half.
Scoop out potato center into a large mixing bowl. Add a half cup of grated Cheddar cheese and a quarter cup of bacon crumbs.
Add enough milk to help this mixture blend or add 1 cup of sour cream with a quarter cup of chopped chives.
Blend.
Or add your favorite combinations.
Put mixture back into potatoes and bake at 450° for about 30 minutes or until tops of potatoes get slightly browned.
Serves 8.

title: best ever pot roast
directions: Place pot roast in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cut potatoes and carrots (enough for the number you want to feed).
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over the top of the meat.
Add water to vegetables. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 new glass flowerpot and real or artificial flowers.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar in pan.
Add water and cook over medium heat until clear.
Add jello.
Remove from heat and cool. Place fresh-cleaned strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour cooled strawberry filling over.
Refrigerate about 3 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients.
Beat on medium speed 1/2 minute.
Bake for 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: chocolate-peanut butter squares
directions: Bring Karo syrup and sugar to a boil, then add peanut butter. Stir to mix well and add Rice Krispies.
Press into cake pan. Melt milk chocolate in microwave for 2 minutes.
Spread over mixture.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix all together and place in greased muffin tins.
Bake in preheated 400° oven about 20 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix well and chill.
(I add 1/2 teaspoon salt.)

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots tender-crisp.
Cut into lengthwise strips. Combine rest of the ingredients in a skillet; heat.
Stir until bubbly.
Add carrots; cook and stir 2 minutes, until glazed.

title: sand cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and form into roll.
Refrigerate.
Slice thin and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: blonde brownies
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, melt butter.
Add brown sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Whip butter and cheese till fluffy.
Add sour cream and green onion to mixture.
Beat with electric mixer till blended.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside. Combine cake mix and sugar.
Add oil and sour cream.
Blend.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of first mixture over the batter. Pour in remaining batter and top with rest of first mixture.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: beef bourguignon(serves 24)
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge meat.
In a large, heavy skillet over high heat, brown meat on all sides in butter and oil.
This will have to be done in several batches, adding butter and oil as needed.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour pineapple with juice in bottom of pan.
Spread the cherry pie filling over this.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the pie filling.
Sprinkle the nuts over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese casserole
directions: In greased 6-cup souffle dish, combine crackers, cheese and mushrooms.
In medium bowl, mix eggs, milk, onion powder, parsley flakes and poultry seasoning.
Pour over mixture in souffle dish and stir.
Bake for 50 minutes or more at 350°.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make cake according to directions.
Remove 1 cup batter before baking.

title: delicious swirl cake
directions: Mix your cake mix and bake; after baked, poke holes throughout cake.
Mix strawberry jello with pop; pour into cake letting it soak through all of the holes.
Refrigerate until it sets up. After it sets up, take the Cool Whip and box of pudding and mix together.
When cake sets up, put the Cool Whip-pudding mixture on top.
It is simply delicious.

title: chinese chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: Marinate chicken in soy sauce and ginger 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In nonstick wok or skillet, heat oil over high heat.
Add marinated chicken and stir-fry for 2 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, remove chicken, leaving juices in the pan. Add peppers, mushrooms and onions and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add pineapple and chicken and stir-fry another 2 to 3 minutes. Vegetables should be tender-crisp.

title: camper's stew
directions: Saute ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer about 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Wash and hull berries.
Pour boiling water over.
Let stand until water is pink, less than 5 minutes.
Put in colander and drain.
Put berries on to cook 3 minutes, without sugar or water (3 minutes from boiling point); stir occasionally.
Add 3 cups sugar; boil 3 minutes.
Add 3 more cups sugar; boil 3 more minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook all ingredients 2 to 3 hours. About 1 hour before serving, add one package frozen mixed vegetables and 3 diced potatoes. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: miss may craver's taffy
directions: Combine ingredients and boil until it will crack on a toothpick when placed in cold water, like ice.
Place on a greased platter or marble slab and let cool until a dent can be made in it when pressed with a finger.
Gather in a lump and pull with fingertips until light and porous.
Roll
in long, thin strips and cut in 1-inch pieces.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Pour into greased cake pan.
Leave in refrigerator overnight. Heat oven to 350°.
Put slices of Velveeta cheese on top. Bake 1/2 hour and serve.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion.
Add corn, beans, chiles, tomatoes, Taco seasoning, Ranch dressing mix and water. Simmer and serve with cornbread.

title: fast mexican supper
directions: Simmer beans, chili and Velveeta cheese 30 minutes.
Dice tomatoes, onions, lettuce, olives, jalapenos and grated cheese. Add whipping cream to bean mixture and simmer 10 minutes.
Layer chips on plate and add bean and chili mixture.
Top with condiments.
Fast and feeds a large group!

title: shortbread crust
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Blend in butter.
Add nuts. Lightly spray baking dish with Pam.
Press dough into bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pan) until lightly browned.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole; set aside. Boil potatoes in water until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain. Place in large bowl and mash.
Add butter, lemon and vanilla extracts, cinnamon, nutmeg, milk, sugar and coconut.
Mix thoroughly.
Add eggs, stirring until well blended.
Pour into casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Let cool about 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients except cabbage and hold out 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Core heads of cabbage.
Put in boiling water and cook until limber.
Drain and cool.
Peel off large veins.
Place meat on cabbage leaves and roll up. Place in pan and cover with the other tomato sauce that has been thinned down with some water. Cover and cook about 2 hours at 325°.

title: coconut pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9-inch round layer pan, blend 1/4 cup butter and brown sugar.
Place in oven for 5 minutes to soften.
Remove from oven; add pineapple and coconut.
Mix and spread in even layer over melted mixture in bottom of pan.
Set aside.

title: easy family beans
directions: Saute 2 slices bacon.
Add 1/4 cup chopped onion and continue to saute.
Drain fat.
Combine bacon, onion, beans, catsup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and dash of garlic powder.
Bake in casserole at 375° for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in (don't beat) sugar, pecan pieces, cracker crumbs, baking powder and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pie pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cover top with whipped cream and let stand for 4 to 6 hours.
Keep refrigerated.
(This recipe came from a Texas cousin who is an excellent cook.)

title: custard pie
directions: Prepare pie crust. Bake at 450° for 8 to 12 minutes. Remove from oven and cool.

title: fay's chocolate pie
directions: In double boiler, combine sugar, flour and cocoa. Stir well. Add in milk, beaten eggs and salt. Stir thoroughly. Make sure no lumps in mixture. Constantly stir mixture until thickens, approximately 20 minutes. Take off heat. Add vanilla and butter, blended well. Pour into all ready baked pie crust. Let cool for about 1 hour.

title: tapioca fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Add orange juice to reserved juice to make 3-cups liquid.
Cook with tapioca until thick.
Cool.
Fold in fruit.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: chickie's "hamburger stuff"
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onions. Drain excess fat.
Add canned ingredients to pan.
Mix, then add peppers (cut into long strips) and all seasonings.
Mix well. Cover with lid.
Cook over low to medium heat for about 1 1/2 hours (until peppers are soft). Serve over white rice.

title: cinnamon snails
directions: Trim the crusts from the bread slices.
Spread one tablespoon of the cream cheese on each slice of bread.
Roll up bread slices with cream cheese on the inside. Cut each roll into thirds.

title: seashell macaroni(hot dish)
directions: Heat skillet and add together onion, celery and green pepper. Fry together until tender, 5 minutes, then add hamburger and let brown lightly in vegetables.
Cook 2 cups of seashell macaroni in 6 cups of water until tender.
Add to this, peas, corn, green beans and hamburger mixture, drained.
Add one large can of stewed tomatoes; mix good all ingredients.
Warm on medium heat.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and use as a dip for any kind of fruit.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Preheat oil to 370°.
Combine next 6 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Spoon onto won ton skins; fold diagonally into triangle. Moisten edges with water and press to seal.
Seal other 2 corners together.
Deep fry until golden brown; drain.
Serve warm with sweet and sour sauce and Chinese mustard.
May freeze and reheat in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Fry the ground beef until done.
Drain the red kidney beans and add it and all other ingredients.
Simmer on medium heat at least 2 hours.
Feeds approximately 6.

title: cheese and pickle spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Use as spread for sandwiches or crackers.

title: pumpkin mousse
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given and blend in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Garnish as desired.

title: salsa cheese dip
directions: Whisk cheese and salsa together.
Add sour cream and whisk. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Blend
all
ingredients
together except whipped cream. Chill overnight.
Fold in whipped cream just before serving.

title: date roll candy
directions: Combine sugar, cream and salt.
Cook until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Add dates and continue cooking until mixture separates from pan when stirred (about 2 minutes).
Add pecans, coconut and vanilla.
Beat until cool.
Pour on a wet cloth and from into a roll.
Cut roll in slices when cool.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press ground beef in casserole dish.
Press diced onion into ground beef.
Place Tater Tots on top of onions.
Mix milk and soup together; pour on top of Tater Tots.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet; saute onion and broccoli until tender.
Add soup, milk and rice.
Mix well.
Add Cheez Whiz and remove from heat.
Pour into baking dish and put in oven for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yorkshire style beef
directions: If roast is a triangular-shaped piece, cut 2 horizonal slits about 2 inches apart almost to other side to make two two deep pockets.
Stuff mushrooms, garlic, salt and pepper into pockets. Season outside of roast with a little additional salt and pepper and roast as directed.
If roast is rolled and tied, carefully unroll.
Sprinkle mushrooms, garlic, salt and pepper over unrolled roast.
Re-roll and re-tie.
Season outside of roast with a little additional salt and pepper.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of meat.
Place roast, fat side up, on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Roast at 325° for 1 3/4 hours or 160° on thermometer for medium.

title: venison jerky
directions: Partially freeze venison; slice thin (1/4-inch thick and 4 to 6-inches long)
No-fat.
Mix all ingredients and pour over meat in a large plastic bag.
Refrigerate 1 day turning often.
Remove from bag and drain on paper towels; place on rack with pan underneath.
Dry in a slow oven (140° to 220°) for 3 to 4 hours.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Sift flour and measure; add soda, salt and spices and sift again.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, then applesauce. Add flour mixture, then add fruit and nuts.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Bake in 2 piece tube pan lined with wax paper.

title: grated potato casserole
directions: Wash potatoes and boil with bay leaves and salt. Cool, then peel. Grate potatoes in baking dish.

title: orange pineapple bread
directions: Boil water and add dates; reduce to simmer and set aside. Combine jam, pineapple, honey, egg whites and vanilla.
Remove dates from water and add to mixture.
Sift flours, soda and salt together.
Add to orange mixture.
Pour into greased bread tin. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add beaten egg, sugar and dates and cook for 6 minutes.
Mix remaining 3 ingredients.
Pour cooked mixture over dry ingredients.
Mix.
Roll in balls.
Roll in remaining coconut.

title: marshmallow fudge brownie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add (sifted) dry ingredients together.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 8 x 12-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and put marshmallows on top.
Return to oven for 3 minutes.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add ingredients. Mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: heavenly hyampom cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately to sugar and Crisco mixture; beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 4 greased and floured pans in a 350° oven.

title: hot crab dip
directions: *Make sure all of the shell is out of the crabmeat.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni. While it's cooking, chop up onion, tomatoes and pepper and peel and chop up cucumbers. When macaroni is done, drain. While it's still warm, put in the tomato, pepper, onion and cucumber mix. Add dressing. Put into refrigerator. Let chill. When chilled, you may want to add more dressing from the 2nd jar and serve.

title: turtle cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare chocolate cake as package directions.
Pour 1/2 of cake batter in pan and bake 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: mock apple pie(no apples needed)
directions: Roll out half the pastry and line a 9-inch pie plate.
Place crackers in prepared crust.

title: fried peach pies
directions: Mix together peaches, sugar and margarine; cover with water. Cook to a thickened sauce.

title: hamburger casserole #1
directions: Pat hamburger into sides and bottom of casserole dish to form a shell.
Pour stuffing in the center.
Cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pie (pie makes own crust)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, melt margarine and sugar, mix.
Add flour, vanilla and coconut.
Heat well again.
Pour into two 8 inch greased pie pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 - 50 minutes.

title: arcadia shrimp and linguine
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients (using 1/2 garlic) together and simmer until juice is reduced and thickened.
In clarified butter, saute shrimp with other 1/2 garlic for 2 minutes.
Remove shrimp from butter.
Put sauce and pasta in skillet with butter and heat until pasta is soft.
Mix with shrimp.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and parsley.

title: laredo supper
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion and green peppers; cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with corn chips if desired.
Serves 4.

title: raspberry yogurt cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and the margarine.
Press evenly in ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 10 minutes; cool.

title: punch
directions: Combine ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Can be placed in decorative mold for freezing.
If frozen, place in punch bowl and add the ginger ale.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: any-fruit coffee cake
directions: In a saucepan, combine choice of fruit and 1 cup water. Simmer, covered, about 5 minutes or until fruit is tender.
Stir in lemon juice.
Mix the 1 1/4 cups sugar and cornstarch; stir into fruit mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and shape into small balls.
Cook for 10 minutes at 400°. Makes about 60.

title: baked lima beans in sour cream
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Drain and cover with fresh water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and cook until tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Drain again and rinse under hot water.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Dab butter over hot beans.
Mix brown sugar, salt and dry mustard.
Sprinkle over beans.
Stir in molasses.
Add sour cream and mix gently.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: eggnog
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a blender.
Pour mixture in a pitcher.
Add the whole milk.
Chill for 3 hours.
Whip the table cream and fold into mixture.
Adjust for more sugar or whiskey at this time.

title: grandmother's coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add buttermilk.
Beat in eggs. Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell. Cook 10 minutes at 375°.
Lower temperature to 300° and cook until done, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peach-a-berry cobbler
directions: For topping stir together flour, 1/2 cup sugar and baking powder. Add milk, and 1/4 cup butter or oleo all at once. Stir until smooth, set aside.

title: candy apples
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in pot; bring to a boil (300°). Put in cinnamon flavoring.
Put sticks in apples.
Dip apples; set aside to cool.

title: macaroni supreme
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Heat soup, add pimento, peppers, onions and mayonnaise.
In casserole dish, layer macaroni, sauce mix and cheese.
Repeat if necessary.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no sugar cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes on low heat.
Add margarine; cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Drop by spoonful on greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Delicious for dieters and diabetics.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Melt oleo and add the other ingredients.
Let come to a rolling boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and beat with spoon until mixture starts to thicken.
Then drop on foil.
(You have to hurry.
It gets hard fast.)

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple together well.
Add pecans and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip and keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: sunday night soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain. Stir in onion; saute until soft. Add remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes.

title: ruth's pound cake
directions: Mix the sugar and shortening. Add eggs and mix well. Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove immediately from pans; cool on wire racks.
Freezes well.

title: purple cow drink mix
directions: You will need a blender.
Mix the ingredients in blender for 1 minute.
Drink.
Enjoy!
Serves approximately 20 children.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Flatten rolls on a large cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned at 350°.
Let crust cool.

title: brown sugar pecan pie
directions: Blend all of the ingredients and put in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450°
for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: marble brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt and set aside.
Melt margarine and blend in brown sugar, white sugar, vanilla and water.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
After chocolate chips melt, swirl through mixture with a knife.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and oatmeal.
Combine both mixtures.
Add chocolate chips, nuts and chocolate bar.
Shape into golf ball size cookies.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart on 375° for 6 to 8 minutes. Makes 112 cookies.
Can be halved for 56 cookies.

title: broccoli beef casserole
directions: Clean broccoli, cut into pieces and steam until done.
Cook rice according to package.
Brown meat and drain.
Mix all together; add soup in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and top with cheese.
Reheat to melt cheese.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pea pickin cake
directions: Break up segments
and
mix
all ingredients well.
Put mix in three layer cake
pans and bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Use your own favorite filling or icing.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in medium strips.
Cook in salted water until tender. Drain.
Melt oleo and stir bread crumbs into melted oleo, coating well. Set aside.
Into a buttered baking dish, put half the cabbage, soup, half the cheese and remaining cabbage. Top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes until crumbs are browned in a 375° oven.

title: sauteed fresh shrimp
directions: Clean shrimp.
Saute in skillet over medium-high heat with scallions, salt and paprika in margarine, stirring until opaque (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Serve with lemon butter sauce, which can be made with melted margarine and lemon juice.
Serves 4.

title: patio punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the ice cubes and the ginger ale. After all ingredients are well mixed, add the ice cubes to chill the mixture.
Don't add the ginger ale until just before serving.

title: skillet fish with vegetables
directions: In a large skillet, heat corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir frequently; cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, green pepper, basil and black pepper, stirring occasionally.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: nelda's corn bread
directions: Mix sugar with beaten eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add melted butter and milk.
Beat up quickly and bake in large buttered 9 x 13-inch pan in a very hot oven (400°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
This makes 1 large pan which will cut into 21 squares.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine in order all ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased pie plates; bake for 45 minutes or until brown. Makes one 10-inch pie or two 9-inch pies.

title: crab cakes
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients until well blended and shape into patties. Brown in frying pan.

title: sticky pull aparts
directions: Combine butter and maple syrup in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle nuts evenly over bottom of pan.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Place close together on syrup and nut mixture. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 to 15 minutes until biscuits are golden brown.
Invert on sheet cake serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: no crust pizza
directions: Drain mushrooms, adding water if necessary to make 1/3 cup liquid.
Combine liquid, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add ground chuck, oregano and half the mushrooms.
Mix lightly.

title: favorite shortcake
directions: Soften shortening by stirring.
Sift dry ingredients into shortening.
Add 2/3 cup milk; mix until flour is dampened.
Beat vigorously 2 minutes.
Add remaining milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Bake in paper-lined 9 x 12-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and tomato casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain well.
Combine this with ham, vegetable and 3/4 cup cheese.
Place in a 2-quart greased casserole pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Top with remaining cheese for the last 5 minutes.

title: detective stew
directions: Brown meat and chopped onion.
Drain grease.
Add tomatoes and soup.
Chop cheese in small pieces for easy melting and add to meat mixture.
Cook rice and drain.
Add to meat and cheese mixture after all cheese has melted.
Serve over Fritos in individual bowls.
(Mixture may be frozen.)

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: In a skillet, cook beef, peppers, onion and salt; stir on medium heat until browned.
Drain well.
Add cheese and heat until melted.
Remove from heat and add eggs and tomato sauce.

title: trash
directions: Mix in paper bag or large bowl the Rice Chex and peanuts. Melt and stir the chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo.
Pour chocolate mixture over other mix.
Shake vigorously.
Pour powdered sugar over and shake again.
Store in covered plastic container.

title: coconut cake or muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 13x9-inch pan or into muffin tins. Bake for 45 minutes, less time for muffin.

title: granny's cornbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and milk.
Add flour sifted with salt and baking powder.
Add cornmeal, stirring only enough to mix.
Fill greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut buster parfait dessert
directions: Put 1/2 of crushed cookies in 9 x 13-inch pan, spread ice cream over this while the caramel is cooling.
Pour caramel layer over ice cream, top with nuts and remaining cookies; freeze until hard.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13 cake pan with nonstick spray. Spread coconut in pan. Layer nuts on top of coconut.

title: grandma's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl sift together first three ingredients and set aside.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar; add vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Set aside to cool but not congeal.
Crush the graham crackers and mix with melted oleo. Beat together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Put evaporated milk in freezer to get cold.
Whip milk.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water and 1 1/4 cup cold water.
Add pineapple and miniature marshmallows.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: cherry torte from grandma
directions: You will need 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make a crust of graham crackers.
Crush crackers.
Add butter or margarine.
Line bottom and sides of pan saving some for top.
Boil cherries, then mix cornstarch, sugar and eggs.
Add to cherries and boil until thick. Serve plain or add a dab of whipped cream or ice cream.

title: charcoal-broiled sirloin steak
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Slash fat edge of steak at 1-inch intervals.
Place steak in pan large enough to allow steak to remain flat.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour over steak.
Cover.
Chill 2 to 3 hours, turning several times.

title: fillo sausage-egg bake
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, melt margarine. Saute red pepper, onion, and mushrooms until tender; remove from skillet. In small skillet, brown sausage over medium heat until no longer pink; drain. Add to mushroom mixture. In medium bowl, beat eggs lightly; stir in Monterey Jack cheese and mushroom-sausage mixture. In another medium bowl, combine broccoli, ricotta cheese and parsley flakes. Heat oven at 350°. Unroll fillo sheets; cover with plastic wrap or towel.

title: c d q bread
directions: Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Add buttermilk, 2 1/2 cups flour, shortening, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend 30 seconds on low speed.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, stirring in remaining flour.
Knead 5 minutes or about 200 strokes on generously floured board.
Roll dough to 18 x 9-inch rectangle.
With side of hand, press each end to seal.
Fold ends under loaf.
Place seam side down in pan.
Brush lightly with butter.
Let rise in warm place (85°) for 1 hour.
(Dough in center should come about 2-inches above pan.)
Preheat oven to 325° and place oven rack in lowest position.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pan and brush with butter.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In a large bowl combine sweet potatoes, butter and milk.
Mix all other ingredients with sweet potatoes just until blended.
Do not overmix.
Pour into crust.
Bake 350 for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: rosie's spicy chicken
directions: In hot oil, brown chicken.
Drain fat.
Meanwhile, combine all ingredients, except the last 3, in a bowl.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 35 to 45 minutes, turning chicken occasionally.

title: veal chops pizzaiola
directions: Set out a large heavy skillet having a tight fitting cover. Heat in skillet olive oil.
Wipe with a clean, damp cloth and then slowly brown on both sides in skillet veal rib or loin chops. Meanwhile, combine tomatoes, garlic, oregano, salt, pepper, parsley, white wine and water.
Slowly add tomato mixture to browned veal.
Cover skillet and cook slowly for 45 minutes or until meat is tender when pierced with a fork.
Substitute 2 pounds beef round steak, cut about 3/4-inch thick for the veal chop.
Cook slowly about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: sunday french toast
directions: Arrange bread in single layer in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. In medium bowl, with rotary beater, beat eggs with milk, orange juice, sugar, vanilla and salt until well blended.
Pour over bread.
Turn slices to coat evenly.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
In hot butter in skillet, saute bread until golden, about 4 minutes on each side.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Crumble ground beef in a 2 quart microproof casserole.
Cover with casserole lid and cook on HI for 5 minutes, stirring once during cooking time.
Pour off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce and water; mix well.
Spread 1/3 of the meat sauce in 12 X 7 inch microproof baking dish.
Arrange half the uncooked noodles over sauce.
Spread with half of the Ricotta cheese.
Top with 1/3 of the meat sauce.
Sprinkle with 1 c. Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers with remaining noodles, Ricotta cheese and meat sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Double-wrap tightly with plastic wrap. Cook on HI for 15 minutes.
Cook on 50 for 12-15 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Cook on HI for 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
6 servings.
Total cooking time:
34-37 minutes.

title: kent county (maryland) hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crab and 1/2 cheese. Fold in crab and 1/2 of cheese; add a little milk to make creamier, if desired. Sprinkle top with cheese and Old Bay.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers. Makes a lot. Can divide and use 1/3 for omelet filling.

title: favorite supreme salad
directions: Mix dry jello in Cool Whip.
Stir in cottage cheese and pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: herbed meatballs
directions: Marinate ground turkey in 1 tablespoon of Worcestershire sauce, thyme leaves, 2 tablespoons of the broth and 1 tablespoon of the cornstarch.
Let stand in the refrigerator for 15 minutes to one hour.
Form meat into meatballs, 1/2 inch in diameter or larger if you prefer.
Place on broiling pan so that juices and fat drain away.
Broil for 10 minutes.
(Do not turn meatballs.) Saute mushrooms and onions in oil until onions are opaque.
Add meatballs, remaining Worcestershire, thyme and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup cold water and stir into meatballs until sauce is just thickened.

title: green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Brown onion in bacon fat.
Stir in chicken broth and beans and dill weed, simmer, covered, for 35 minutes.
Add tomatoes and bacon, heat 5 minutes.

title: beef 'n potato bake
directions: Press firmly into bottom and sides of baking dish, combined potatoes, oil and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes. Brown beef and drain.
Add gravy mix, water and garlic salt.
Bring to slow boil.
Add vegetables and cook for 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup cheese.
Place into potato shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: mrs. phillips' lemon cookies
directions: Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: bubble bread
directions: Melt margarine and mix in brown sugar.
Add cinnamon and the butterscotch pudding mix.
Mix well.
Grease a Bundt pan or spray with Pam cooking spray.
Pour the nuts in the bottom of the pan. Drop in the bread rolls one at a time, arranging neatly.
Pour the pudding mixture over dough rolls.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese pie
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Slice onion.
Shred cheese.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, milk, flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg. Mix well; set aside.
Alternately layer onion, broccoli and cheese in pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over layers.
Place pie on cookie sheet and bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barley soup
directions: In large pan, melt butter or margarine.
Add celery, onion and barley; saute for 5 minutes.
Turn down heat and quickly stir in flour.
Add chicken broth.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour, until barley is tender.
Just before serving, add chopped parsley, thyme and sour cream or evaporated milk.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and crackers.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Melt butter, crush one tube of crackers, and combine.
Spread over potato mixture and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tomato vegetable soup(diabetic)
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add everything except macaroni. Add macaroni last; cook until tender.

title: chicken breasts and rice
directions: Pour chicken broth over raw rice in a large casserole dish. Dot with butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain mushrooms and add to casserole. Put chicken on top of mix.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over all.
Dilute chicken soup with milk and spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: hamburger pot pie
directions: In a skillet, heat 1 tablespoon Crisco.
Add ground beef and onion; cook until meat is brown.
Stir in green beans, soup and seasonings.
Pour filling into onion pastry-lined pie plate. Place top crust over pie filling and bake.

title: chicken enchilada soup
directions: Stir all together and warm.
Serve with sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: lavender cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put eggs, margarine, sugar and lavender into blender and run on low until well mixed.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients and stir until blended.
Drop dough by 1/2 teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned; cool on rack.
Blend enough rosewater into the confectioners sugar to make a smooth frosting.
Ice cookies and let them sit until frosting is firm.
(I add food coloring to make them lavender.)
Can also decorate top with edible flowers.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Sift together flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream shortening until soft.
Beat in egg and molasses and gradually add sugar.
Sift dry ingredients over creamed mixture; blend well. Form in small balls by rolling them tightly.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes.
If less spicy cookie is desired, use only 1 teaspoon ginger.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and flour.
Add milk; stir until smooth. (Cook in a double boiler.)
When hot, add egg yolks and cook until thick.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Top with meringue.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate or shred potatoes in food processor.
Remove and let drain to remove excess moisture.
(You may sprinkle lightly with lemon juice to prevent potatoes from turning dark.)
Process onion and garlic in food processor.
Add seasonings and remaining ingredients.
Add to potatoes and mix together.

title: angel toffee dessert
directions: Core an apple.
Stuff the opening with peanut butter, cream cheese or cheese spread.
Chill.
To serve, slice crosswise.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make brownies as per package directions and cool.
Before assembling, make chocolate mousse.
To layer, crumble 1/3 brownies in bottom of a large bowl; follow with 1/3 of chocolate mousse, 1/3 of Cool Whip and 1/3 of Skor bars.
Repeat, ending with Skor bars.
Keep refrigerated until ready to use.

title: casserole quiche
directions: Cut each tortilla into 8 wedges.
Prepare as directed for Crisp-Fried Tortilla pieces; set aside.

title: ground beef and vegetable soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir undrained tomatoes, corn, carrot, green pepper, mushrooms, bouillon granules, oregano, 3 cups water and dash of pepper into the cooked meat mixture.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 5 servings.

title: hamburger and green bean soup
directions: Brown ground beef; don't drain.
Add water and bouillon cubes. Cook until boiling, about 10 minutes.
Cube potatoes (bite size). Add to burger and drain green beans and add also.
Boil until potatoes are soft.
Let simmer about 15 minutes.
You can also add more water and bouillon cubes.

title: dad's stuffing for fish
directions: Mix, then stuff flounder, trout or snapper.

title: seashell pasta and shrimp
directions: Saute vegetables in butter.
Add broth, water and cream cheese.
Add mushroom soup.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until done.
Season to taste.
Thicken with flour paste and serve over shell pasta.

title: crispy caramel corn
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over popcorn; mix well.
Bake, covered, in roaster 1 hour at 250°.
Stir occasionally.

title: pickled okra
directions: Boil vinegar, water, salt, and sugar for 3 minutes.
Pack okra in pint jars with first 4 ingredients.
Fill with hot liquid. Seal jars.
Place in hot water bath, bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.

title: sour cream noodles
directions: Cook noodles; drain and rinse.
Place butter in skillet and cook onion and ground beef until brown.
Drain fat.
Add spices and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Mix together sour cream and cottage cheese.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt butter and mix with crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Don't bake.

title: german kuchen
directions: Cream butter and oleo.
Add sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix in flour, salt and vanilla.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan.
Reserve about 1 cup batter to put on top.
Cover with Thank You brand pie filling or any thickened fruit filling you wish.
Drop reserved batter on top with spoon.
Do not cover completely; it will spread.
Bake at 350° (plus or minus) until brown, 50 minutes.
Make sure dough is done on top.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add zucchini and walnuts.
Pour into greased bread pans and bake at 350° for one hour or until done.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix dry gelatins together.
Add boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Chill until firm, about 1 hour.
Cut into shapes or squares.
Remove.
If left in same pan, bottom will be tough.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk.
Add lemon juice.
Drain pineapple. Stir pineapple into mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: date bran bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour bottom of an 8 x 4 or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl, combine quick bread mix, bran cereal, buttermilk, honey and egg. Stir by hand 50 to 75 strokes until dry particles are moistened.
Pour into prepared pan. Sprinkle wheat germ over batter.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool upright in pan 15 minutes, remove and cool on wire rack. Store tightly covered overnight in refrigerator.
If desired, serve with cream cheese and apricot preserves.
Makes 12 servings.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cover bottom of pan
with
olive
oil.
Chop onions and garlic and saute.
Add sausage and cook over low heat until it turns brown.
Add tomato puree and
1 small can of water.
Add large can of tomatoes and 1/2
of
that
can
of
water.
Add chopped pepper and basil.
Bring to
a boil, then simmer for 4 hours. Garnish with fresh grated Parmesan cheese.

title: shortcut lasagna
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add meat and cook, breaking up with wooden spoon.
Drain grease.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, sauce mix and vegetable juice.
Bring to boiling; lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Cover bottom of oiled pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) baking dish with a thin layer of meat sauce.
Then add a layer each of uncooked noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, ending with meat sauce.
Cover casserole tightly with heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Set on a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; let stand 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and chopped parsley.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: megan's pink salad
directions: Mix all together and chill 2-3 hours.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted butter; line bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours in refrigerator or 1 hour in freezer.
Mix powdered sugar, 2 sticks of butter and eggs; beat 8 to 10 minutes until it is like buttercream.
Spread on cracker crust.
Drain pineapple; spread on cream mixture.
Slice bananas over pineapple layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle chocolate syrup on top; sprinkle on chopped nuts and garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in flat baking dish.
This makes 2 large and 1 small pan.
Cover with butter crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and crumbs are brown. Serves 40.

title: eight layer salad
directions: In a glass baking dish, 9 x 12-inch, layer in order.
Cover with cheese.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: carrots delight
directions: Combine carrots, onion and 1 tablespoon butter in glass dish. Microwave, covered, on High for 12 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Mix parsley flakes, lemon rind, salt, sugar and pepper in small bowl.
Add to carrots.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon butter; mix well.
Microwave, covered, on High for 2 minutes longer. Yield:
6 servings.

title: big "a's" pecan pie
directions: In a medium bowl, beat the eggs slightly.
Mix in the next 5 ingredients and beat lightly until you have a smooth blend.
Stir in the pecans.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center of pie comes out clean.
Cool at room temperature and serve slightly warm.

title: marjorie's cocoa cake
directions: Add cocoa to water; stir and cool.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add the cocoa water and vanilla.
Sift cake flour and soda together; add alternately with sour milk, beating with each addition.
Bake in greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch) at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix everything but flour, chocolate chips and oatmeal together.
Add these last.
Bake in oven at 350°.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Put in flat dish and heat in microwave.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Return to microwave until cheese is melted, about 2 minutes.

title: easter breakfast egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs. Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini italian-style(microwave)
directions: Cut unpared zucchini crosswise into halves, then lengthwise into fourths.
Place salt and zucchini slices in 1 1/2-quart microwavable casserole.
Sprinkle with salad dressing and herb seasoning.
Cover tightly and microwave on High (100%) 3 minutes. Stir.
Cover and microwave until tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: woodman's wife cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together, then fold in box of Jiffy cornbread mix (8 1/2 ounce).
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: strawberry ice
directions: Combine sugar and 1 cup water into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add strawberries and lemon juice.
Pour into ice cube tray; freeze.
Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: three bean chili
directions: Brown meat with onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: scallopine with peppers
directions: Dredge chicken in flour.
Cut peppers in slices.
Saute chicken in 2 tablespoons of oil until golden (5 minutes each side).
Remove from pan and keep warm.
Add 1 tablespoon oil; add peppers and saute until tender.
Add crushed garlic and saute 1 minute.
Stir in wine and vinegar, stirring to coat.
Spoon over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: mustard-glazed ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into a 9 x 5-inch loaf in shallow baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Meanwhile, prepare Ham Loaf Mustard Sauce.
Drain fat from pan.
Pour Mustard Sauce over loaf.
Bake 30 minutes more, basting with sauce occasionally.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Use Cream Cheese Frosting if desired.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill overnight.
Serve with vegetable dippers or bread sticks.

title: cut-out cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cream of tartar, salt and soda together. Cut in margarine and shortening as for pastry.
Add eggs, milk and lemon extract which have been stirred together.
Mix until smooth. Roll thin on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Arrange on greased cookie sheet and bake in oven at 375° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Melt butter and saute onion and celery.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Makes 2 casseroles.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix
granulated
sugar,
flour	and salt.
Add rhubarb; mix. Put
into an ungreased 8 x 8-inch dish or cake pan.
Mix together in a dish the oats, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter. Sprinkle over
rhubarb.
Bake
in
a
oven
for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies from amish cookbook
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill dough well.
Form balls on cookie sheet (ungreased) and flatten crossways with a fork dipped in white sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: broiled chicken
directions: Rub salt, pepper and paprika into chicken.
Brush with butter and bake until golden brown at 450° to 500° for 1/2 hour or until leg moves.

title: tamale pie
directions: In a large skillet cook and stir ground beef, sausage, onion and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, corn, ripe olives and seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Pour into an ungreased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch or a 2 quart casserole.
Mix cornmeal, milk and eggs and pour over meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: to can pickles
directions: For pickles, don't let them boil, just real hot and let cover on canner for a while.
Add dill, also onion to your taste.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring sugar, water and 2 teaspoons cinnamon to a boil.
Drop in Ritz crackers.
Boil two minutes.
Pour into unbaked crust. Dot with butter or oleo and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: green chilies and beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Salt lightly.
Add onion and cumin. Simmer until onion begins to tenderize.
Add the soups, tomatoes, corn, chilies and cheese.
Continue to simmer over low heat until cheese melts.
Layer this mixture in a casserole dish with Doritos.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: udon(japanese noodle soup)
directions: Cook Udon noodles in a large pot of boiling water until tender.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Saute chicken in oil or broth until done.
Mix dressing according to directions.
Add onions. Put 3/4 of dressing in bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken on dressing.
Mix soup with one can of water.
Pour over chicken. Top with remaining dressing.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: blueberry ambrosia
directions: Mix all together in a bowl.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: southern style chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken with salad dressing.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Yields 18 servings.

title: punch for a bunch!
directions: Dump all in a large punch bowl. If you want it spiked, add 1 quart of vodka.
Serves at least 60 (6 ounce) glasses with ice cubes.

title: apple julip
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.
Garnish with lemon slices and mint sprigs.
Yields 7 cups.

title: david eyre pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, milk and egg in a mixing bowl and beat lightly, leaving batter slightly lumpy.
Melt butter in an ovenproof 12-inch skillet.
When very hot, add batter to skillet and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and briefly return to oven. Pour lemon juice on top and serve immediately.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage and onion with water and vinegar until crispy done. Drain. Mix brown sugar, flour, salt, pepper and vinegar. Add to bacon; stir. Add cabbage and heat thoroughly. Taste. Correct seasoning, salt, pepper, vinegar and brown sugar.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water the morsels and butter. Remove from heat; stir in brown sugar.
Cool 5 minutes, then blend in 2 eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to the butter and sugar mixture.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and melted oleo together.
Add cocoa, flour and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: pea pickin' cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes in round cake pans.
Cool.

title: ham rolls
directions: Place the cheese on top of the ham slices.
Wrap the asparagus in ham and cheese.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together. Place Ham Rolls on a baking dish.
Pour the mixed ingredients over the ham.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: italian frittata
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in
small bowl; beat well.
Coat a medium nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Saute red peppers and broccoli for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove mixture from skillet and set aside.
Add egg mixture to skillet and cook over low heat until set.
Do not stir. Top with cooked vegetable mixture, alfalfa sprouts and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Cover tightly and let stand for 3 to 5 minutes until cheese melts.

title: sheri's salmon casserole
directions: Set oven to 350° and grease a 2-quart casserole.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: very good chow mein
directions: In a large kettle, brown meat.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Stir.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours on low heat. Serve over rice.

title: anise cookies
directions: In a small bowl, beat eggs until light and fluffy with an electric mixer for about 10 minutes, then add sugar, a tablespoon at a time, beating well after each tablespoon.

title: yum yum pudding
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a buttered dish on top of stove. Let set 5 minutes to make a syrup.
Mix next 6 ingredients to make a batter.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 300° in 8 x 8-inch pan for about 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: orange breakfast rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, sprinkle yeast over water.
Let stand 5 minutes until yeast is dissolved.

Stir in 1/4 cup sugar, salt, sour cream, 6 tablespoons butter and eggs. Add 1 3/4 cups flour and beat 2 minutes with electric mixer. Stir in remaining flour to make soft dough. Cover and let rise in a warm, draft-free place until double in bulk, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: marinated cabbage
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed for 2 minutes.
Add salad oil and bring to boil again.
Pour over shredded cabbage and onions that have been sliced thin and layered.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Next day turn mixture once and serve.

title: savory grilled potatoes
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients. Divide equally and place on 6 (12-inch) squares of foil.
Seal, forming a packet.
Grill over medium coals 25 to 30 minutes. This is also good fried in skillet.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Add raw potatoes, top with 1 stick melted butter.
Sprinkle cinnamon over sweet potatoes.
Top mixture with 1 box yellow cake mix.
Mix water, and the brown and white sugar in medium bowl and pour over cake mix. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and moistened bread in a large bowl; set aside.
Brown sausage slowly, adding margarine, onion and celery. Cook until onion is tender.
Pour over bread mixture.
Add eggs, seasonings and about 2 cups of broth.
Mix well, adding more broth until all is soft and moist.
Mix in raisins, if desired.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes, or until firm and heated through.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: You will need 24 cupcake liners.

title: tomato treat(punch)
directions: Combine ingredients and serve cold.

title: cranberry orange scones
directions: In food processor fitted with steel blade, combine flour, sugar, sour cream, butter and orange juice.
Pulse until well mixed and a sticky dough is formed.
Remove from processor bowl to another large bowl.
Stir in dried cranberries and toasted pecans. Turn out onto well floured surface and knead lightly until no longer sticky.
Divide into two portions.
Pat each portion to a circle that is about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut each portion into 8 wedges.
Place these wedges on ungreased baking sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush the tops with melted butter.
Serve with jam or preserves of choice.

title: nut horns
directions: Mix last five ingredients all together for filling.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and flour like pie dough (can add a little more flour if needed).
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Wrap in Saran or foil and refrigerate a couple hours or overnight.
Roll each ball out in powdered sugar.
Put 1 teaspoon nut mixture in center and roll in powdered sugar again.
Place on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Clean and crisp lettuce. Tear into bite size pieces.
Boil peas and cool.
Layer first 5 ingredients in large cake pan in order given (lettuce, peas, celery, onion and carrots).
Blend sugar and mayonnaise.
Pour over lettuce. Garnish with cheese and bacon which has been fried crisp, drained and broken into small pieces.
Let stand overnight.

title: cotolette di maiale(pork cutlets)
directions: Marinate cutlets in shallow pan or dish with vinegar and lemon juice for 1 hour. Remove and dry with absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Beat eggs lightly and blend with 2 tablespoons water.
Mix in garlic, parsley, salt, pepper and basil.

title: irish halloween supper
directions: Cook potatoes and pass through food mill.
Chop scallions finely, both green and white parts.
Cook 5 minutes in milk.
Beat this mixture into mashed potatoes until smooth and fluffy.
Season to taste and serve a large mound on each plate.
Place a knob of butter on top of each mound.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix and place in greased pan.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350°. Frost.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken or London broil. Marinate at least 8 hours.

title: cranberry butter
directions: Mix all and serve on your favorite muffins, rolls or biscuits.

title: pie crust
directions: With fork, mix first 4 ingredients.
In a separate bowl, beat remaining ingredients.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with fork until moistened.
Mold dough into 5 balls.
Chill for 15 minutes before rolling.
Can leave balls in refrigerator for 3 days or freeze.
Makes five 9-inch pie shells.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with mixer until frothy.
Slowly add Eagle Brand milk, sugar and vanilla.
Pour into freezer container and add milk to "fill line".
Stir well.
Then begin freezing with ice and ice cream salt.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until smooth.
Add eggs and coconut and nuts.
Beat well, stir in pineapple, fold in bread cubes.
Spread mixture in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot or cold.

title: orange flavored nuts
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, mix sugar, water and corn syrup. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook to 238° or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball which flattens on removal from water; remove from heat.
Mix in food coloring, marshmallows and orange flavoring, stirring until marshmallows are melted.
Add nuts and stir until well coated.
Turn onto waxed paper.
Separate nuts while still warm.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: macadamia nut
directions: Drain mandarins, add syrup to water to make the 2 cups. Dissolve Jell-O in fruit water and mandarin juice.
Add ice cream and stir until melted and mixture begins to thicken.
Add mandarins, pour into a mold, freeze.
Serves 8.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Blend together the sugar, salad oil and vinegar.
It is best when this mixture is heated and then left to cool.
When cool, pour over sauerkraut mixture and let stand several days in refrigerator.
This salad should be kept under refrigeration.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan in 350° oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter evenly.
Spread chips, nuts and coconut flakes over crumbs.
Drizzle sweetened condensed milk over everything.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and gelatin until dissolved.

title: chili-o pot roast
directions: Combine Chili-O mix with onion seasoning.
Mix with the tomatoes.
In large ovenproof Dutch oven, add the boneless rump or chuck roast.
Baste with tomato mixture.
Cover; bake at 325° for 2 hours, basting occasionally or until almost tender.
Add the frozen stew vegetables.
Bake, covered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally until meat and vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Fully cook sausage; drain and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Melt margarine and saute onion until soft.
Add water, bouillon, tomatoes and green pepper; bring to a boil, then add sausage, zucchini, linguine and Parmesan cheese.
Cover; cook until soup is simmering, stirring to prevent pasta from sticking.

title: very berry ices
directions: Puree fruit in a blender.
Heat water and sweetener together to a clear syrup.
Pour into blender; mix completely.
Freeze in plastic containers or as popsicles.
A great treat on a hot summer day.

title: beef stew
directions: Roll beef in flour; brown beef in shortening in heavy saucepan.
Add water, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add onions, carrots and potatoes.
Cook 30 more minutes.
Add peas and cook until tender.
Serves 6.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce in deep bowl as bottom layer. In layers, add celery, pepper, onion, and peas. Do not toss. Spread mayonnaise evenly over peas. Sprinkle with sugar and cheese. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Sprinkle bacon over salad before serving.

title: hominy luncheon dish
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; add paprika, chili powder, sugar, cornmeal and salt.
Add tomato juice to beef mixture; stir well.
Simmer several minutes.
Place hominy in greased casserole. Pour mixture over.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and browned slightly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven.
Pour salad oil into skillet, heat until hot. Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Pour half the mix into pan or skillet.
Sprinkle with half (1 cup) cheese.
Pour in rest of bread mix and add other cup of cheese on top.
Bake at 370° for 35 minutes or until fork comes out easily.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Take out and set aside.
Brown meat in skillet and mix with onion and pepper.
Pour over shredded cabbage in casserole dish.
Spoon tomato soup over top.
Do not dilute soup.
Cover and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chops
directions: Wash chops; dry slightly.
Season to taste.
Heat shortening to moderately hot temperature.
Flour chops; slip into hot grease. Cook chops, covered, during entire cooking time, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Chops should be tender and juicy.

title: grilled bread
directions: Soften margarine and stir in dressing mix.
Spread on bread. Grill or broil until golden.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sweet potato surprise cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
Combine oil and sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add hot water and dry ingredients (which have been sifted together).
Beat well.
Stir in potatoes, nuts and vanilla and beat well.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Bake in three 8-inch layer pans at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool and frost.

title: rosemarie's apple cider punch
directions: Bring to a boil the apple cider, brown sugar and cloves.
Add caramels.
When melted, add rum.
Serve with whipped topping, while warm.

title: fancy cashew brittle
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe bowl (2-quart glass with a handle), stir together the nuts, sugar and corn syrup. Microwave, uncovered, at High until mixture is light brown, about 6 to 8 minutes, stirring well halfway through.

title: creamed puff cake
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Add flour and salt. Stir until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each until mixture is smooth.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread dough in pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Pat down during baking to keep even.
Cool.

title: salmon loaf or patties
directions: Combine; place in buttered dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Or shape into patties and fry in pan until golden brown.

title: sunrise squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble sausage into medium skillet. Cook over medium heat until browned, stirring occasionally.
Drain off any drippings.
Spread bread cubes in greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish; top with sausage and cheese. Whisk eggs, milk, salt and mustard until well blended; pour over cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting into squares; serve hot.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 servings. You can make this meal ahead and refrigerate overnight before baking.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, spice, well beaten eggs and milk; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, soups and shrimp.
Simmer 30 minutes or longer (the longer, the better!).

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs in mixture.
Add dry ingredients and add buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° until it begins to brown.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake until done, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: manicotti marinara with peppers
directions: Cook vegetables in skillet with oil until soft.
Add sauce and spices.
Cook 3 minutes.
Spread half of sauce in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In bowl, stir together 1 cup Mozzarella, Ricotta, egg and Parmesan cheese.
Fill tubes with Ricotta mixture; place in dish.
Pour remaining sauce over pasta; sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 7.

title: no-peek stew
directions: Place ingredients in crock-pot on low for 8 hours.
Or bake in oven in glass dish for 3 hours at 325°.
Serve over cubed or mashed potatoes or noodles.
Will hold if Dad is late for dinner!

title: garden rice
directions: Thinly slice zucchini.	Drain corn.
In a 12-inch Dutch oven, saute
onions
and	zucchini in bacon fat until tender. Add corn and the remaining
ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients and add milk, egg substitute, honey and oil.
Mix until just moistened.
Add nuts, raisins and apples.
Fill greased muffin tins (or use muffin papers).
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar if desired.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes.
Yields one dozen muffins.

title: mexican red rice
directions: Saute rice in oil until golden.
Add chicken broth, garlic powder, onions and tomato paste.
Stir to mix well.
Add corn, cover and cook until liquid is absorbed.

title: light velvet cake(low-fat)
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Gradually add egg, beating well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Make low-fat cream cheese icing.

title: croutons
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish. Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until croutons are dry.
Stir once during heating.
Croutons will become crisper as they cool.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust per directions on package.
In medium skillet, cook and stir meat until brown; drain off fat.
Stir in salt, oregano, pepper, crumbs, 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce, onion and green pepper.
Put on pie crust.
Spread Cheese Topping over filling.
Bake for about 30 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Stir together the remaining tomato sauce and the chili sauce; serve with pie.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy saucepan. Gradually stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Cook 1 minute. Beat egg yolks.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into yolks. Add remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly, 30 seconds.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, vanilla and 1 cup flaked coconut.
Pour into pastry shell. Cool completely.
Top with beaten egg white frosting or whipped cream.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chocolate chips with 14 ounces of almond bark in 2-quart bowl on High 2 minutes. Stir and continue microwaving until smooth, about 2 minutes. Stir in marshmallows, peanuts and cereal.
Pour into greased pizza pan.
Top with cherries and coconut.
Microwave remaining 2 ounces of almond bark with oil about 1 minute. When smooth, drizzle over coconut and pizza.

title: meringue for pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy. Add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time. Continue beating until stiff and glossy. Add vanilla.

title: cooked spiced apples from hickory bridge farm
directions: Pare apples and slice them thick.
Place in saucepan in 1 cup water.
Cook over medium heat until soft.
Stir carefully to prevent sticking.
Add sugar and margarine and cook a few more minutes.
Pour into bowl and add spices.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put in 1-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great with baked ham!

title: trillionaire candy
directions: In saucepan, combine topping and pecans over medium heat. Stirring, bring to boil and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and allow to cool 5 minutes.
Spoon about 1 1/2 teaspoons mixture on top of each cracker.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Melt chips over low heat.
Remove.
Using tongs, dip bottom of cracker in chocolate.
Transfer to waxed paper. Refrigerate about 1 hour.

title: arroz sazonado
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, brown rice in oil until golden, stirring.
Add 1 3/4 cups of water, sausage, onions, tomato sauce, salt and chili powder.
Heat to boiling.
Stir.
Cover and simmer over low heat 25 to 30 minutes until rice is tender.
Stir with fork.
Add 1/4 cup of water if rice is too dry.
Fluff rice with fork and stir in cheese.
Serve with Spicy Tomato Sauce.

title: mandarin chicken
directions: Saute chicken 3 minutes on each side.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange oranges around chicken.
Stir onions and garlic in remaining margarine saute.

title: layered taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off drippings. Stir in beans, 1/2 cup salad dressing, chili powder and salt. Cover, reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes. In medium bowl, combine remaining 1/4 cup salad dressing, tomatoes and bell pepper and mix lightly.

title: perfect meatloaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into a loaf. Pour ketchup over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: butterless, eggless, milkless cake
directions: Bring to a boil (5 minutes) all ingredients, except the flour and baking soda.
Cool completely.
Add flour and soda mixed in a teaspoon of hot water.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.

title: morning glory muffins
