directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in grated carrots, raisins, nuts, coconut and apple.
Beat together eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture just until moistened.
Spoon batter into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: boneless chicken breast
directions: Combine mayo and mustard.
Dip chicken in mixture and put in pan.
Pour soup on top and spread.
Sprinkle stuffing on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla and butter thoroughly.
Pour into a buttered 1-quart casserole dish.

title: curried egg salad
directions: In a bowl, stir together the mayonnaise, the curry powder, the celery salt, the Tabasco, the cumin, the mustard, the lemon juice and the chutney.
Stir in the eggs, the celery and the scallions and season the salad with salt and pepper.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Mix catsup, whiskey, onion and brown sugar in frying pan or skillet.
Bring to boil.
Add hot dogs which have been sliced into bite-size pieces.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 1 hour.
Stir about every 10 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add taco mix; cool.
Add other ingredients and toss with dressing.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; drain and place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Melt 6 tablespoons butter and blend in flour; slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Heat to a boil.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with grated cheese.
Melt 3 more tablespoons of butter and stir in bread crumbs.
Pour on top of the cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and salt.
Mix flour and coconut.
Add to the first mixture,
Melt butter and pour over mixture.
Add water and pour into the pie shell.
Bake at 325 degrees for one hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop shrimp. Mix all ingredients. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: aunt sarah's soup
directions: Continue cooking on low heat for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Makes a large amount and will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: mexican hot chocolate
directions: Combine chocolate, milk and cinnamon in a saucepan.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted. Remove from heat.
Using an egg beater, beat until foamy.
Serve hot in large mugs.
Makes 6 cups.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce; simmer 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles; drain.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together over low heat until forms soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Fold in peanut butter and beat.
Pour into pan or oblong dish.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: beef 'n' corn casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add soup and cream cheese; stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted. Add corn, pimiento and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits; cut each in half crosswise.
Place biscuits, cut side down, around edge of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are browned.
Serves 6.

title: julianne's favorite cherry pie
directions: Lay 1/2 crescent rolls in bottom of pie dish.
Pour cherry pie filling on top.
Lay rest of crescent rolls on top.
Sprinkle sugar and melted butter on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.

title: stir-fry goulash with rice
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add salt, garlic powder, lemon pepper, butter, carrots, broccoli, onion and beef broth; cook until tender.
Mix flour with water to make a thin paste to use for thickening.
Serve over rice.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Combine ingredients and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Add sliced roast beef and heat thoroughly.
Serve on buns.

title: "dirt" dessert
directions: Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar; set aside.
Mix instant pudding, milk and vanilla together.
Stir Cool Whip into pudding mixture.
Then add cream cheese mixture.
Layer crushed cookies and mixture in a bowl or pan, alternating layers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
May be frozen and reheated in oven.

title: gail's caesar salad
directions: Combine egg yolks, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, olive oil and garlic cloves.
Let set 1/2 hour.
Cool before serving. Pour over ripped romaine lettuce.
Add croutons, grated Parmesan or Romano cheese and black pepper.

title: penuche frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and beat until lukewarm.
Add vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread. If it becomes too thick, add about 1 teaspoon of cream.
Icing for 2 layer cake.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add tomato soup mixed with baking soda. Rinse can with hot water. Blend in flour, spices and baking powder. Add raisins and salt.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour, spices and salt.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add flour mixture to buttermilk.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each addition.
Add jam and blend into batter with wooden spoon.
Bake 3 (9-inch) layers at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows. cook until marshmallows melt and mixture is syrupy, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Beat biscuit mix, sugar, egg, orange juice and rind vigorously.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes (bread is done when toothpick comes out dry).
Cool before slicing.

title: pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops. Brown the chops. Layer chops in a casserole dish. Spread onion slices on top. Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chops. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour and thirty minutes. You can use beef steaks or venison steaks if you desire.

title: zucchini pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla, oil, zucchini, flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Stir in pineapple and raisins.
Add nuts and mix well.
Bake in a tube pan or 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or until done (ovens vary).

title: taco baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes, prick skins with a fork and microwave 10 to 12 minutes on High.
Remove and let stand.
Meanwhile microwave ground chuck about 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain fat and break apart.
Stir in taco sauce.
Split potatoes and put on individual serving dishes. Spoon 1/4 of the meat mixture on each potato.
Top with sour cream, cheese, onion, lettuce and tomato.
Serve immediately.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Boil water; add margarine until melted.
Add flour; mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Dough rises high, forming a cup.
Let cool.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add onion, rice, beef consomme, water and salt.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sunflower seed cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients and then sunflower seeds.
Form into a roll 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper or Glad Wrap and chill 1 to 2 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Slice and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground turkey and Italian sausage.
Add spaghetti sauce; simmer.
Combine Mozzarella cheese and Ricotta cheese in a separate bowl and eggs.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with vegetable spray.
Layer uncooked lasagna noodles, meat mixture and cheese mixture 3 times, ending with the cheese mixture.
Add 3/4 to 1 cup hot water around edges.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: beer batter perch
directions: Mix ingredients together, except fish, in large bowl, making light batter.
Dip fillets in batter, then place in deep fryer or frypan.
Cook in hot oil or bacon grease.
Let fish cook for 3 minutes, turning when golden brown.
For crispy fish, cook a bit longer.

title: shrimp and vegetable paella(serves 4)
directions: Add water to defatted broth to make 2 cups.

title: boiled custard
directions: Add milk slowly to other ingredients.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Chill at once.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Bring all ingredients, except chicken, to a boil.
This makes enough to marinate two good size fryers.
Marinate at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: triplet's favorite casserole
directions: In skillet lightly brown ground beef and onion.
Drain. Meanwhile, prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions.
Transfer ground beef mixture and macaroni and cheese to a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add corn and tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Top with cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir together the first 5 ingredients. Add flour and add other ingredients. Cook at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken. Crumble Ritz crackers and mix with melted butter.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Cut up cooled chicken into small pieces over top of crackers.
Mix soups, sour cream, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage ball hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix the 3 ingredients by hand.
Pull off small chunks and rolls into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 75.

title: steamed blue crabs the truly maryland way
directions: Mix seasonings, vinegar and beer (or water) well.
Put 1/2 crabs in very large pot with rack and tight fitting lid.
*Pour 1/2 of seasoning mixture over top.
Add rest of crabs and remaining liquid.
Steam, covered, until crabs turn bright red in color, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes about 9 to 12 servings, depending upon size of crabs.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain fruit and save juice.
Mix jello in 1 cup boiling water. When dissolved, add 1/3 cup pineapple juice and blueberry juice to make 3/4 cup liquid.
When jello mixture is slightly thickened add fruit and let thicken.
Fold in Dream Whip, pour into mold and let set.
Cool Whip may be used in place of Dream Whip.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion (drain). Add meat and onion mix and all the other ingredients to cooked spaghetti. Pour in extra large casserole or make 2 or 3 casseroles. Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Freezes well.

title: killer pancakes
directions: Mix and pour 1/2 cup in hot, greased pan.
Turn and serve.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add oil, 1/3 cup buttermilk and bananas; beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining buttermilk.
Beat an additional 2 minutes.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cook and frost with favorite icing.

title: cranberry mold salad
directions: Put in mold until chilled.
Put on plate and put cottage cheese out around.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, eggs, butter, Crisco and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Roll dough into walnut sized balls. Roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with small glass bottom dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 12 minutes. I refrigerate my dough after I mix it, for about 1/2 hour.

title: ham and potato soup
directions: In a 5-quart pan, place potatoes, onion, ham and water; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer gently until potatoes are done. Add soup and milk; stir to blend.
Simmer until serving temperature is reached.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand until juice forms. Add beaten egg, then mix in all other ingredients. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Add raisins or nuts if desired.

title: turkey chili
directions: To make a dish of days, take 8 hours of work, larded with interest, intelligence and well being, carefully cutting out with sharp knife all gristle of conceit and envy.
Add 8 hours of sleep mixed with wide open windows.
Stir in 2 hours of gardening; and 2 hours reading of history, poetry and fiction; well blended.

Add 4 hours of companionship and human kindness, season with mirth, bake in old fashioned religion with cover of sympathy and faith; drain off carefully all enviousness and self-seeking; garnish with children's laughter and herb of old thyme respect.
Serve on a platter of everyday life.
No family can get enough of it.

title: sausage puffs or balls
directions: Form into balls. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: almond cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Save 1/3 almonds to cover cheese ball.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together and drain.
Combine with other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: brown meatballs and gravy
directions: Mix ground beef, onion soup mix, rice and Pet milk. When completely mixed, roll into 1 1/2-inch balls. Put oil in frying pan. Place balls in single layer. Fry on medium heat, turning over when brown. Cook until meatballs are browned and no pink in middle. Take meatballs out of skillet. Drain oil out of pan. Mix soup and water in skillet. Add gravy coloring and meatballs. Simmer for 20 minutes on low-medium heat.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Slice stems and ends from peppers; take out seeds.
Blanch in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine ground beef and remaining ingredients.
Stuff peppers and arrange in greased baking dish.
Top with ketchup if desired. Bake in oven at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Smash cookies into crumbs.
Set aside a few for topping.
Melt butter and mix with cookie crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze for 1 hour.
Let ice cream soften.
Place ice cream on top and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Freeze overnight.

title: chocolate coconut balls
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Chill mixture 1 to 2 hours or overnight.
Roll into small balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Dip candy into chocolate and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chips.
Stir in sugar and pour over eggs. Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells which are partially cooked (5 minutes) and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: edinburgh tearoom scones(english recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt in bowl and stir. Add butter and cut in with a pastry blender. Mix in raisins. Measure buttermilk in a 1-cup measure and beat egg in. Add to flour mixture all at once. Mix with a fork until mixture clings together. Form the dough into a ball and turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead gently until smooth, not more than 5 turns of the dough. Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick and cut out with 2-inch biscuit cutter dipped in flour. Place on baking sheet about 1-inch apart. Brush tops of scones lightly with milk and sprinkle with sugar. Bake 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: grandma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Whip together until smooth the sugars, shortening, peanut butter, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to whipped mixture.
Break off dough by teaspoonfuls, roll into ball, place on ungreased baking sheet and mash with fork. (Optional additions: 1 cup chocolate chips, nuts.)
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ready to drink iced tea
directions: (Steep 2 family-size tea bags in 3 quarts of water.)

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Heat milk and sugar to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Add cocoa.
Beat with wire whisk until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter, vanilla and salt. Makes 3 cups.
(My family loves this over hot biscuits for breakfast!)

title: ham loaf
directions: *These are approximate measures.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into 3 small unbaked pie shells (or 1 large and 1 small).
Bake in 325° oven for about 1 hour.

title: squash relish
directions: Combine squash, onion and salt and let stand 1 hour, then squeeze out.
Grind ingredients.
Bring vinegar mixture to a boil and add squash mixture and bring to a boil again.
Add one 7 ounce jar pimento.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa with flour.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until custard sets.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in Crisco in large skillet. Remove meat, leaving in a little fat. Stir in flour, soy sauce, catsup, pepper and beef cube dissolved in hot water. Heat to boiling point. Add beef strips and onion rings. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add green peppers, mushrooms and juice.
Simmer an additional 10 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Rinse crab meat with cold water and dry on paper towels.
Mix top 6 ingredients well and spread on muffins.
Freeze for at least 30 minutes.
They may be kept frozen for weeks.
When party time arrives, broil them until they puff up and are bubbly and slightly brown.
They just take a few minutes.
Serve hot.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Brown meat and drain off excess fat Add seasonings and cook until tender.
Simmer for 1 hour on low heat.
Grind oysters and mushrooms; add to meat mixture.
Moisten bread with water; squeeze out excess water.
Break up and stir into dressing.
Mix well and continue to cook about 30 minutes more on very low heat.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
(Salt in oysters will make a difference.)
Serve hot or can be served cold on a sandwich.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except bread crumbs, in a casserole.
Place bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: luscious fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail, reserving pineapple juice. Combine juice, pudding mix and Tang.
Stir well.
Add all fruit to this mixture.
Chill.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil hen; debone.
Add other ingredients.
Cook together about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese with fork; add other ingredients, saving some pecans to cover unmolded ball.
Place in bowl and chill overnight.

title: strawberry lemon squares
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar, and butter until blended.
Press into bottom of 13x9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, and 1/4 cup milk until blended.
Spread over crust. Pour 2 3/4 cups milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mixes and blend well. Pour over cream cheese layer.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.
Cover with whipped topping.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar together until creamy.
Add gradually, the remaining ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Place 1 inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press down with spoon. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool and sift 10x sugar on each.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut out stems and chop up (put aside).
Mix ingredients together and add chopped stems.
Stuff mushrooms; cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 fresh peach pie
directions: Stir flour and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix together.
Pour over peaches in a bowl.
Stir until peaches are coated.
Pour in shell.
Bake for 35 minutes at 400°.

title: dofu meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well and allow to stand for 10 minutes. Form into balls and roll in additional bread crumbs.
Fry in 1/2-inch of oil, turning frequently.

title: swiss fondue
directions: Rub inside of fondue pot or saucepan with cut edge of garlic, then discard.
Simmer wine in fondue pot, blend in soup.
Combine Swiss cheese and cornstarch then stir into soup mixture.
Heat until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Great with cubes of French bread and apples.

title: smothered shrimp
directions: Heat oil and add all other ingredients.
Fry for 6 minutes over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 more minutes.
May serve with white rice.
Serves 6.

title: sausage and apple stuffing
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, heat sausage until brown.
Drain and save 1/4 cup of sausage drippings.
Return to pan.
In drippings over medium heat, cook apples, onion and celery until done, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add sausage meat and remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake, if desired, for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and chill.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all together.
Store in airtight container.
Use 3 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.
Really good on a cold winter day.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix all together.
Roll into balls and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Pour in crust and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Mix beans and taco mix and heat until warm in the microwave. Spread on a large plate and cool (I use a bright blue plate).
Add a few drops of lemon to the avocados and spread on the beans. Layer on the remaining ingredients in the order listed. Top with grated cheese and alfalfa sprouts. Serve with corn chips and salsa.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Mix in flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt.
Fold in carrots, raisins and some nuts.
Bake in 2 layers for 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.
Frost with caramel icing.

title: frozen fruit squares
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise and beat with mixer until blended.
Stir in fruit cocktail.
Whip the cream until soft peaks form.
Fold cream into the fruit mixture.
Pour into a 12 x 7 1/2-inch dish.
Cover and freeze.
To serve, remove salad from freezer and let stand at room temperature for about 10 minutes. Cut into squares.
Serve with lettuce.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pineapple and coconut pie
directions: Mix and pour in raw pie crust.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven until brown and done.
Will shake a little in middle.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Must use counter top electric mixer.
Mix first five ingredients on low speed until lumps are dissolved, then beat at highest speed while adding butter.
Mix until blended.
The longer the frosting is beaten, the lighter it will be.
You must have a strong mixer!

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate peppermint pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and blend into creamed mixture.
Melt chocolate, cool and beat into creamed mixture.
Add peppermint extract.
Turn mixture into crust.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Spread with whipped cream, to which powdered sugar has been added.
Top with crushed peppermint candy.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain
corn
well.
Add
sour
cream, grated cheese and onion to corn and mix.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Cover with Ritz
cracker
crumbs and squeeze liquid butter over the crumbs or
melt
stick
of butter and pour over the top. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: aunt dorothy's fudge scotch ring
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips with condensed milk over hot, not boiling, water.
Stir occasionally until mixture begins to thicken.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Cool for about 1 hour. Butter ring mold and place the 3/4 cup walnut halves around bottom.
Spoon mixture in mounds onto walnuts.
Decorate with remaining 1/4 cup walnuts.
Chill in refrigerator until firm enough to slice.
Keeps well in tightly covered container after it is once set.

title: cheese quiche with spinach
directions: Spread 3/4 cup of the cheese in the bottom of the shell.
Beat milk, eggs and seasonings in a bowl to blend.
Just before baking, spread the drained spinach on the cheese.
Pour liquid to fill the shell to within 1/8-inch of the top.
Sprinkle on the remaining cheese and the butter.
Cut into dots.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: creamy orange drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender until smooth.

title: fusilli with chicken and roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix chicken, zucchini, squash, red peppers, salt, pepper, fennel seed, rosemary, garlic and oil in 15 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake uncovered 15 to 20 minutes until vegetables are tender and chicken is not pink.
Cook fusilli, drain and transfer to a large bowl.
As soon as chicken and vegetables are done, broil 4-inches from heat 2 to 3 minutes until lightly browned.
Add to fusilli, along with pan juices and basil, mix and serve.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Serves 4.

title: quick barbecue beef bake
directions: Cook ground beef and 1/2 cup of the onion in skillet until browned.
Drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Spoon into ungreased 9 X 13 baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Set aside.
Mix together baking mix, milk and eggs until blended.
Pour over beef mixture. Sprinkle with remaining onion.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until crust is light golden brown.
Make 8-10 servings.

title: grilled chicken breasts with tomatillo-cilantro salsa
directions: Grill chicken breasts for 4 minutes per side.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Lay pork chops in baking dish. Season with salt and pepper. Top each chop with a slice of onion and lemon, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup. Cover. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer or until chops are tender and brown, basting occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat pie
directions: Fry ground beef with salt, pepper and onion.
Combine with potatoes.
Line pie plate (glass) with one pie crust.
Put a layer of potatoes with meat and a layer of peas and carrots.
Make another layer of each.
Top with another pie crust.
Bake at 400° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie 2
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add syrup, milk, eggs, salt and vanilla. Mix thoroughly. Add coarsely broken nuts.
Pour into uncooked 9-inch pie shell. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat and bake in a 275° oven until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: a different slaw
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar and seeds to a rolling boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Let cook at a low boil 2 to 3 minutes. Cool completely.
Finely shred cabbage.
Slice onion and cut slices in fourths or eighths.
Chop green pepper into small pieces.
Mix lightly and add drained pimento.
Pour vinegar mixture over cabbage mixture and mix.
Slaw should be made 12 to 24 hours before serving and stirred several times.
Keeps in refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: red fish court bouillon
directions: Make a dark brown roux with flour and oil adding just a bit of butter (about 1 tablespoon).
Add onions and stir until browned (beer bottle colored).
Add tomato paste and cook thoroughly.
Add garlic, celery, green pepper, lemon and bay leaves.
Add hot water, a little at a time, up to about 3 cups and let simmer for about 45 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and red pepper.
Add fish and let cook for 20 minutes after boiling begins.
Add parsley and Worcestershire sauce and after boiling returns, cut off heat and let stand with cover on for 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Serves 10.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Do not salt. Pick chicken off bone.
Put aside and save broth.
Melt margarine and stir into dressing.

title: crab sandwich spread
directions: Combine all ingredients lightly.
Spread on buttered bread or toast.
Top with another slice of bread or garnish with pimiento.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add milk and oleo.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Chunk into bite size pieces in large bowl.
Add soup (may also use other creamed varieties), celery and sour cream.
In separate bowl, crush crackers and stir in melted butter.
Spread half of cracker mixture on bottom of a large casserole dish.
Spoon in chicken and top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until edges are bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broil'ems
directions: Split Shredded Wheat biscuit along seam with point of sharp knife to make 2 halves.
Spread with butter or oleo.
Spread mustard thinly.
Top with meat and cheese.
Broil 2 to 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve warm.

title: fanny farmer fudge
directions: Boil sugar and condensed milk for 7 minutes.
Turn off heat and add vanilla.
Beat in
1 package of chocolate chips at a time. Add butter; stir well.
Add marshmallow cream and nuts.
Spread in jelly roll pan and cut into squares.

title: brownies
directions: Set oven at 350° or 325° to be safe.
Melt chocolate in covered pan over hot water; take off as soon as chocolate melts. In mixer, put 1 stick margarine.
Add sugar gradually, along with eggs, one at a time.
Add warm chocolate and mix.
To get all of chocolate out of pot, add a big spoon of mixture to the chocolate in pot and mix and clean out with spatula.
Add flour, vanilla and salt to mixture.
Stir and spread evenly in greased large 11 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in center of oven.
Do not overbake!

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, peanuts and salt in an 8-cup measure.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and blend well.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
When brittle is cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes 16 servings.
Per serving:
133 cal, 2 gm protein, 5 gm fat, 2 gm carbohydrate, 0.6 cholesterol and 79 mg sodium.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and beat with electric mixer for two
minutes.
Pour
into
Bundt
pan and bake at 350° for approximately 1
hour.
When done, turn onto a plate and cover to keep moist.

title: veal-chicken parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs, garlic powder, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and m.s.g.
Pound veal-chicken to 1/4-inch or less in thickness.
Dip cutlets in beaten eggs and pat lightly in bread crumb mixture.
Fry in butter until brown.
Remove veal-chicken from pan.
Combine tomato sauce, sweet basil and sherry in frying pan.
Place veal-chicken into sauce.
Let come to a boil, then lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes in a covered pan.
Place Mozzarella cheese on cutlets and cover for 10 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: hot cheese canape
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on bacon thins.
Broil for 1 minute.
Watch carefully.

title: crazy berry pie
directions: Mix ingredients, except pie shell.
Put in pie shell and chill until served.

title: "scrabble"
directions: Melt butter, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt. Pour over cereal; mix good.
Bake 1 hour at 300°; stir often! Cook with top on pan.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into two 9-inch layer pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together the eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Pour into 2 medium size loaf pans, greased and floured. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: almost homemade lemonade
directions: Put lemonade, sugar and fruits in a gallon container; mix well.
Chill and enjoy.

title: cobbler
directions: Cut up butter in a pan; put fruit over that.
Combine flour, Crisco and milk.
Roll it out long and lay it on top of fruit. Spread a cup of sugar on top.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon. Pour water over it and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan butterscotch cake
directions: Prepare pudding as directed and cool.
Add 1 egg and mix with cake mix.
Grease a 13-inch by 9-inch baking pan and pour in batter.
Cover with butterscotch morsels.
Tap into batter slightly but do not mix.
Mix brown sugar, flour, oleo, and nuts. Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat sugar, salt and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each one.
Add lemon.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes, on middle shelf, until set.
Should be brown slightly.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into well greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Remove from oven.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Mix together brown sugar, syrup, oleo and salt in pan on stove until it boils.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and stir.
Put popcorn in a large grocery bag.
Add mixture and shake it up. Cook 1 minute in microwave and shake.
Cook 1 minute in microwave and shake.
Cook 1/2 minute in microwave and shake.
Cook 1/2 minute in microwave and shake.
Let cool.
Crunch it up in the bag.
Pour in bowl and enjoy.

title: southwest cranberry relish
directions: Mix and serve over cream cheese with crackers such as Wheat Thins or as accompaniment for turkey, chicken or ham.

title: pepper casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, green peppers and onion.
Cook over medium heat until beef is lightly browned.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, water, Worcestershire sauce, black pepper and rice.
Cover and simmer until rice is done (15 to 20 minutes).
Remove lid and continue cooking until remaining liquid is gone.
Stir in cheese and transfer to a baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: champagne punch
directions: In punch bowl, add over ice all of the liquid except ginger ale.
This you add just before serving.

title: sausage potato casserole
directions: Cook sausage thoroughly.
Combine soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Using 11 x 7-inch baking dish, layer potatoes, soup and sausage.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until potatoes are tender.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato yeast rolls
directions: Mix together warm water, ginger, 1 teaspoon sugar and yeast. Cube and boil potato until tender.
Drain 1 1/2 cups of water and add to the following.
In large bowl, mix sugar, margarine and salt.
When potato and potato water are finished, mash the potato cubes and add potato and water to sugar, margarine and salt mixture while hot.
Allow to cool until lukewarm, beat eggs and mix in.
Add yeast mixture.
Add 4 1/2 cups flour and mix well; add 3 more cups flour.
Use extra 1/2 cup flour and knead into dough.
Shape into rolls; place on pan brushed with oil.
Let rise at room temperature for 2 hours.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: john's spicy shrimp
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and set aside.
Combine water, beer, chilies, garlic, mustard and bay leaves in large pot. Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Bring to a full boil.
Add shrimp, cook for 3 minutes. Serve with sauce.
May be served hot or cold.
(I prefer it cold.)

title: chocolate sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Chill overnight.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost and decorate.

title: coffee punch
directions: Make coffee from ground coffee and water using a coffee maker. Dissolve sugar in 2 cups hot coffee; set aside to cool. Make 2 trays ice cubes from remaining coffee. These 2 steps should be prepared a day ahead. Combine remaining coffee with sugared coffee in a covered container; refrigerate.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together and pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: coconut or chocolate pies
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornstarch (and chocolate if making chocolate).
Separate eggs.
Add yolks and milk (slowly); beat with a mixer.
Cook until thick.
(Can be cooked in microwave.)
Add coconut (if making coconut), margarine and vanilla.
Let stand until cool.
Put in two cooked pie shells.
Sprinkle coconut on top of meringue made from egg whites or grate chocolate from Hershey bar and top chocolate pies.

title: cheesecake tartlets
directions: Mix all together, except wafers, in mixer.
Put on wafer in bottom of each paper muffin cup.
Put mixture on top of wafer. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with filling.
You can use different pie filling.

title: crab or shrimp aspic
directions: Mix jello with soup.
Add vinegar, boiling water and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Let set.

title: peach ice cream(this ice cream is peachy.  nick loves ice cream!)
directions: In a bowl, put ice cream powder.
Gradually add water to powder, stirring until dissolved.
Add milk and almond extract. Freeze in a freezer tray until thick, but not too hard.
Beat with a hand held rotary beater until smooth.
Fold in peach pulp and continue to freeze.
Check and stir frequently.

title: string beans and pearl onions
directions: Place green beans in 1 3/4 quart casserole.
Place onions and cream sauce over beans.
Sprinkle with summer savory.
Use Defrost cycle and cook 7 minutes, stirring once during cooking.
Cook at Full power for 12 to 14 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla and also eggs together.
Melt chocolate and add to creamed ingredients (or use 3 tablespoons cocoa instead of chocolate).
Dissolve soda in ice water and add. Also add salt.
Bake at 350° until finished.
Top with peanut butter icing.

title: chocolate savannah squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs 1 at a time and cream together.
Sift flour with baking soda and add alternately with water and vanilla.
Stir in oatmeal and pecans.
Press mixture into greased 10 x 15-inch pan and bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and while very warm, spread with peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Make a swirl pattern by twisting around on top.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti. Drain and pour dressing and seasoning over while hot. Mix well.
Dice vegetables and mix well. Salt and pepper to taste. Marinate overnight.

title: manhattan cocktail meatballs
directions: Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Put meatballs in sauce. Simmer 5 minutes.
Put in chafing dish.
Serve hot.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as instructed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool. Cut into 1/3 and crumble 1/3 in the bottom of a punch bowl.
Mix together strawberries and put 1/3 on cake.
Put 1/3 of pineapple next.
Put 1/3 (dry) vanilla pudding next.
Put a layer of bananas. Repeat this procedure 2 more times.
On top, spread Cool Whip. Garnish with chopped nuts and cherries.
May spread Cool Whip between layers, if you wish.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until blended.
Stir in raisins if desired.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, sugar and pineapple-grapefruit juice.
Add enough water to this to make 1 gallon.
Make ahead of time and store in refrigerator.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Combine cream soup and water.
Bone and skin chicken breasts. Put rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour cream soup mixture over rice.
Place chicken breasts on top of this.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over all.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: citrus grove punch
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil. Cook for 5 minutes. Cover and refrigerate until cool. Combine juices and sugar mixture. Mix well. Just before serving, stir in ginger ale. Serve over ice. Yield: 6 quarts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth according to package directions. Drain.
Combine peas, bell pepper, salt, pepper, soup, chicken broth and 1/2 cup cheese.
Add to noodles and chicken.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger pot pie(double crust)
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (for metal pie plate 425°).
Sift flour before measuring.
Spoon lightly into nested 1-cup measuring cup and level without shaking down.
Cut Crisco into flour with pastry blender or two knives until mixture is uniform.
Mix onion, salt and water.
Sprinkle on water a tablespoon at a time.
Toss lightly with a fork.
Work dough into a firm ball with your hands. Divide in half and form two flat circles.

title: raspberry tapioca parfait
directions: Follow the directions on the Minute tapioca box, for fluffy tapioca cream, adding a teaspoon of orange vanilla extract along with the vanilla.
Stir well after 20 minutes.
When cold, fold in a half pint of cream that has been whipped.
In parfait glasses, alternate layers of tapioca and 3 or 4 defrosted raspberries and a dribble of juice (about 3 layers of tapioca) and top with a few berries and a bit of juice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: avocado-orange salad
directions: Mix together the vinegar, salad oil and salt; set aside.
Cut avocado into bite-size pieces.
Add to orange sections.
Toss gently with vinegar mixture.
May serve in half shells of avocado, if desired.
Serves 2.

title: peppery cajun stuffing
directions: In heavy 10 to 12-inch skillet, melt 1/4 cup margarine.
Add 1 cup onions, also the red pepper, celery and fennel.
Cook until onions are done.
Add rest of onions.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Heat remaining 1/4 cup margarine in small pan until it turns golden color; add to mixture.
Add rest of ingredients and cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: nutmeg logs
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg and blend until smooth. Add vanilla and rum flavoring.
Sift together flour and nutmeg.
Add slowly to creamed mixture while stirring.
Shape dough in rolls 1/2 x 3-inches.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool.

title: stuffed apples
directions: Core an apple.
Make sure all seeds are gone.
Fill hole with peanut butter and eat apple or slice.
You can also mix a few raisins into peanut butter before stuffing.

title: white enchiladas
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Drain.
Stir in cheese and chilies.
Mix 1/2 sour cream and 1/2 can of soup; reserve for later use.
Mix the remaining cream and soup into meat mixture.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Put meat into tortillas.
Roll and put into pan.
Pour reserved soup and cream on top.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° until well heated.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until creamy.
Mixture will be thick.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook and boil 1 minute in large pan the sugar and milk until most dissolved. Melt in butter and cocoa. Stir in peanut butter until creamy. Turn off heat but leave on burner. Fold in vanilla, oats and nuts. Stir together completely. Scoop into teaspoon-size on wax paper. Cool in fridge until set.

title: crumb topping
directions: With a fork, mix all ingredients well.
Sprinkle over top of quick coffee cake.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook onion in shortening slowly until yellow.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in water.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Add and mix mashed potatoes until smooth.
Stir in Pet milk.
Add grated cheese.
Heat slowly until cheese melts.
Do not boil. Serve hot.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Poach chicken in boiling water for 10 to 15 minutes or until cooked.
Once cooked, take out of water and place in ice to stop the cooking.
Dice chicken and place in bowl.
Chop walnuts, scallions, celery and apples.
Place in bowl with chicken.
Add raisins, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Serve on a bed of lettuce or on a sandwich roll.

title: easy shrimp alfredo
directions: Combine first four ingredients in heavy saucepan; cook over medium-low heat until cheese is melted and onion is tender.
Add shrimp and heat until they turn pink.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: angel food cake
directions: Follow package directions for the egg white packet; while beating add 3 fresh egg whites.
Fold in the flour sugar packet. Add flavoring if desired.
Use large round, square or loaf angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until cracks in top begin to dry.
Invert until cool before removing from pan.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Take large quantities of cheerfulness and let simmer without stopping.
Put in a brimming bowlful of kindness.
Add a full measure of thoughtfulness for others.
Mix in a heaping tablespoon of charity.
Stir well, and carefully strain off any selfishness. Add plenty of smiles and bake in the warmth of a loving heart.

title: golden fruit cake
directions: Wash raisins in warm water.
Cut cherries in half and slice the rest of fruit.
Chop nuts coarsely.
Cream shortening and add sugar gradually.
Cream well.
Add eggs, beaten until very light. Add jelly and mix well.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together.
Dredge fruit and nuts with 1/2 cup of this mixture.
Add remainder to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Add vanilla and stir in fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Line pans with greased heavy paper.

title: chunky chip cookie
directions: In a mixer bowl, cream together butter, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture; blend well.
Stir in chocolate drops carefully so do not break.
Cover the bowl.
Refrigerate dough overnight. Scoop out dough by teaspoons.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet, 1 inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until browned.
Cool slightly, then remove onto rack to cool completely.

title: grandma coffman's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together
diced tart apples and sugar.
In separate bowl, combine
eggs,
oil and vanilla.
Mix with apples.
In a separate bowl,
combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, nuts and cocoa.
Stir this into other ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking
dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: sam's champagne
directions: Chill juice and lemon-lime.
Pour one of each in punch bowl. Make as much or as little as you like.

title: holy ghost sopas(sopas do espirito santo)
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add meat, spices (tied in clean cloth), wine, onion, tomato sauce, mint and salt.
Cover and cook until meat is tender, about 3 hours.
Add cabbage, cut in half.
Cook until tender.
Place bread slices and a sprig of mint in a deep serving dish or pan.
Pour boiling broth and cabbage over bread. Remove meat to another dish or platter.
Serve meat with the sopas. Serves 6 to 8 persons.

title: poppy seed cheese bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve the yeast and sugar in water. Combine milk, shortening and salt; stir in yeast mixture.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto a floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 3 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hour.
Punch the dough down; press into a greased 9 x 13 x 2 baking pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until nearly doubled, about 45 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight or all day.

title: tod's tuna salad
directions: Shred eggs with cheese shredder.
Mix with other ingredients. Serve on lettuce leaf or on toasted bread sandwiches.

title: hangtown fry for two
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add spinach layer to bottom of skillet. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until set.
Fold and top with sour cream and Parmesan cheese.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Spread crescent roll dough on cookie sheet with sides slightly high.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes; cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings until smooth.
Spread on top of cooled crust.
Layer your choice of fresh vegetables on top (press down slightly).

title: brandied fruit starter
directions: Combine all ingredients in a non metal bowl. Cover, let stand at room temperature for 3 weeks. Stir once a week. Serve over ice cream or pound cake.

title: tasty crispy chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces about the size of chicken fingers. Beat eggs and add enough paprika to color and dip chicken pieces in egg mixture.
In a separate bowl, combine instant potato flakes and a generous amount of chicken seasoning.
Now dip chicken pieces in the potato flake mixture and coat chicken well. Fry in vegetable oil over medium heat until golden brown.

title: potato fondant
directions: Add hot potatoes to butter and vanilla.
Add sugar.

title: apple cheese cake
directions: Peel and slice apples; set aside.
Separate eggs; set aside egg whites.
Mix melted butter with egg yolks and sugar.
Add sour cream and cream cheese and mix for 2 minutes.
Add whipping cream, flour and baking powder.
Mix 3 minutes.

title: chimney corner dressing(red)
directions: Grate onion in food processor.
Add other ingredients and beat hard until well blended.
The dressing will begin to turn orange when it is blended enough.
Makes 1 quart and 1 pint.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until tender; drain.
Add margarine, soup, bouillon cube and cheese.
Mix until melted.
Stir in cooked rice.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Boil butter and light corn syrup for 5 minutes on medium heat. Add 1 1/2 cans sweetened condensed Eagle Brand milk.
Mix 1/2 cup flour with the other 1/2 can condensed milk.
Boil slowly until mixture darkens and makes a medium hard ball (240°).
You must stir constantly as it burns easily.
Cook in a heavy aluminum pan. Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet. Cool.
Cut into squares and wrap each piece in wax paper.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: spinach spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Serve in hollowed-out round bread with crackers.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Mix fruit, nuts, flour, sugars and salt.
Add beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add melted margarine and mix again.
Grease and flour cookie sheets.
Drop mixture by scant teaspoonful on cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes until golden brown.
Store baked cookies in airtight container.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: skyline chile
directions: Chop beef very fine as you add water into a large pot or kettle.
Do not brown beef first.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 3 hours, stirring just occasionally.
Cook 1 large package of spiral noodles.
Drain and lay on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour chili mixture over noodles.
Add grated Colby or Cheddar cheese.
Cover and bake in oven until hot and cheese has melted.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until done.
Peel and dice.
Add all ingredients to diced potatoes in a casserole dish. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes and shred.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in potatoes, onion, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Sprinkle flour over top of mixture.
In a heavy frying pan, melt enough shortening to be 1/4-inch deep.
Drop 1/4 cup potato mixture for each pancake into hot shortening; flatten slightly with back of spoon to make thin cakes.
Fry slowly, turning once, for 3 to 5 minutes or until golden and crisp.

title: scott's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix about half of the cake mix, oleo, vanilla and eggs in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix, chocolate chips and nuts.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Melt margarine or butter in large Pyrex baking dish.
Stir in pecans, and bake at 300°, stirring every 10 minutes.
Bake for about 30 to 40 minutes, depending on size of pecans.
Pour onto doubled paper towels to cool.
Store in plastic Baggie-lined coffee can or other metal container.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Boil hamburger; skim off fat.
Add potatoes, carrots, onion, bay leaf and noodles.
When vegetables are done, add tomatoes or juice.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix everything but blueberries.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass pan with a little margarine.
Combine the flour, oats, brown sugar and margarine in a food processor and mix on low until crumbly.
Press in the 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes.

title: fried stuffed jalapenos(a snack for the true cowboy.)
directions: Cut each pepper, making a small slit.
(If your skin is sensitive to jalapeno oil, wear thin plastic gloves.) Remove the seeds.
Carefully wash them, keeping the peppers intact.
Place on a paper towel to drain.

title: aunt jean's meatball sauce
directions: Put meatballs in crock-pot or roaster.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Cook on low 6 to 7 hours or may be baked in oven at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: sausage and cheese muffins
directions: Crumble sausage; cook until brown.
Mix sausage and cheese. Spread over open-faced muffins.
Bake in oven until golden brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined flour and spices; mix well.
Slowly add oats, then raisins.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for a chewy cookie, 8 to 9 minutes; for a crisp cookie, 10 to 11 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 6 to 7 pie crusts.

title: lemon christmas cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add lemon extract and blend.
Add dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add fruit and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour one-third of the batter in a floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. While cake is baking, melt caramels with evaporated milk over low heat.
When cake has baked for 15 minutes, remove from oven and pour melted caramel evenly over the cake.
Sprinkle the pecans and chocolate chips over the caramel.
Pour the remaining cake batter on top and bake for another 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Test for doneness.
Enjoy!

title: pink salad
directions: Mix together and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: hound dog rolls
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
Cut cheese into 1/2 x 1/2 x 3-inch sticks.
Slit each wiener lengthwise, being careful not to cut through bottom or ends.
Insert a cheese stick into each wiener.
Drain shells.

title: vidalia onion rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute onions in margarine in a large skillet until soft, about 10 minutes.
Boil rice in water in saucepan for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Place onions, rice, cheese and half and half in greased 10 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: grandma's pancakes
directions: Put flour and sugar in a bowl and warm milk in a cup; beat egg into milk. Gradually add to flour mixture. Add oil. Pour in greased frying pan; fry until golden brown.

title: lemon kuchen or orange
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add flour, lemon rind, eggs, baking powder and lemon juice.
Drop in heated oil and fry. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Spread half of the crushed cookies in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Whip together butter and cream cheese. Add sugar and Cool Whip; fold together and set aside. Prepare pudding using vanilla and milk. Add pudding mixture to cream cheese mixture and mix thoroughly. Pour over cookie crumbs. Sprinkle top with remaining crumbs. Chill 1 to 2 hours or overnight before serving. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: quick cheese dip
directions: Melt equal parts of chili and Velveeta cheese together.
Serve in fondue to keep warm.

title: pizza
directions: Take the bread put the saus on the bread.

title: "old time" ham casserole
directions: Skin and parboil potatoes. Slice and layer into casserole dish (first layer). Follow by thinly sliced onion, separated into rings, next picnic ham, cut into slices (approximately 3/4 to 1-inch pieces).
Repeat layers of potatoes, onion rings, ham, sliced mushrooms. Top with frozen peas. In a separate bowl, mix mushroom soup, milk and grated Swiss cheese.
Pour this over other ingredients in casserole dish.
Heat in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour until browned and bubbly.

title: easy blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder together.
Add eggs, milk and oil, blending thoroughly.
Stir in blueberries.
Place into greased muffin tins or foil cupcake liners.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: better than sex cake
directions: In medium saucepan, cook pineapple with sugar until thick and syrupy, about 20 minutes.
When cake is done, remove from oven and pierce top with fork at 1-inch intervals.
Pour on pineapple mixture and spread over cake evenly.
Cool completely.
Combine milk with pudding and blend until thick.
Spread over cool cake. Beat whipping cream, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cake.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Sprinkle with coconut before serving (optional).
Pig out!
Delicious!

title: lemon bisque
directions: Mix graham crackers and sugar.
Melt margarine and mix with cracker mixture.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Stir lemonade into ice cream. Pour over crust.
Freeze.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased, shallow baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes or well done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: homemade sausage gravy(dedicated to my sister sherri)
directions: Fry sausage and leave in grease when done.
Add approx. 2 Tbsp. additional grease or oil.
Add flour, stir constantly until flour is browned.
(Add salt & pepper if desired) Stir in about 4 c. milk and continue stirring.
Reduce heat stirring until gravy is the thickness you want it to be.
(Add milk for thinner gravy, or corn starch & water to thicken.)

title: mom's chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain; put half of macaroni in bottom of casserole dish, half of chicken pieces next, put several teaspoons of gravy over top.
Next, add half of tomatoes and then half of cheese.
Repeat layers, salt and pepper top.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 50 minutes.

title: no cholesterol apple cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick coating.
In a large mixing bowl, combine sugars, oil and egg whites.
Beat with a wooden spoon until well blended.
Add flours, oat bran, baking soda, cinnamon and allspice.
Stir just until moistened. Stir in shredded apples.

title: quick quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour and mayonnaise.
Add eggs, then everything else.
Pour into pie shell and bake about an hour until golden brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, onion, oats, catsup, milk, salt and Worcestershire sauce together well.
Make loaf and top with the catsup, mustard and brown sugar mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Add everything else. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: steak supper
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Dredge in flour.
Brown well on both sides in hot oil.
Place meat in baking dish.
Quarter potatoes; arrange in dish with meat.
Pour off excess fat in skillet; scrape browned drippings left in pan and add tomato sauce, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over meat and potatoes.
Sprinkle parsley over mixture.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 30 minutes or until steaks are tender.
Serves 4.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Sift flour and measure and set aside.
Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar together well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add flavoring last. Pour into 10-inch tube pan and set in cold oven.
Turn oven to 325° and bake for 1 hour, then turn oven to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients good for sauce.
Cook beef and onion until brown.
Layer in sheet cake pan.
Put chips in first, ground beef, sauce, then cheese.
Repeat.
Cook at 350° until hot all way through.

title: noodles
directions: Add flour, enough to make dough stiff enough to make dough stiff enough to roll out.
Let dry and cut into thin strips.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1/2 pieces and measure 3 cups in a bowl. Sift flour, sugar and salt together and mix with rhubarb.
Let stand while rolling out 1 crust and fit in pie pan.
Stir beaten eggs into rhubarb mixture and pour into crust.
Dot with butter. Make a lattice top crust of strips of dough.
May sprinkle a little cinnamon or nutmeg over rhubarb.
Bake 10 minutes at 425° and about 30 minutes at 325°.
Filling will be a little bubbly when done.

title: spaghetti squash
directions: Wash squash and cut in half; remove seeds carefully.
Place cutside down on baking sheet.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Using fork, pull (spaghetti like) squash.
Place in 2-quart buttered casserole.
Butter top and sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Serve.

title: glazed carrots
directions: About 25 minutes before serving, in pan over medium heat in 1 inch of boiling water, heat carrots and 1/4 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Cover and cook 15 minutes, or until tender-crisp; drain and add butter, sugar, 3/4 teaspoon salt and nutmeg.
Return mixture to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until carrots are glazed.

title: crab mold
directions: *Frozen imitation crab (thawed) may be substituted for canned crab.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and dip them in milk.
Then coat with Bisquick.
Place in oiled or nonstick spray-coated baking pan. Sprinkle with paprika and seasoning salt as desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered, and without turning.
Coating should be crisp at serving time.
Serves 6.

title: dreidel sandwiches
directions: Spread the peanut butter on two slices of bread.
Slice the apple or banana into thin strips and put them on the peanut butter.
Top with other two slices of bread.

title: chicken bundles italian style
directions: Chop the chicken breasts and saute with the green onions in olive oil.
Add the spinach, Ricotta cheese and rest of ingredients.
Spray muffin tins.
Place an egg roll wrapper in each tin.
Fill with the chicken mixture.
Fold over; brush with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: magic dessert bars
directions: Layer all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows, margarine and cooking oil.
Mix all ingredients well and pack in angel food cake pan.
Cool and cut.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Mix dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise and mix thoroughly.
Add well drained vegetables and mix well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs to form crust. Add layer of sliced bananas. Next, mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice for next layer. Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle coconut on top of Cool Whip. Sprinkle with pecans. Add sliced cherries and refrigerate until chilled.

title: mother's lemon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Combine ingredients except egg whites in a bowl. Pour in baked pie shells and bake for 10 minutes: remove from oven. Cover with meringue made of whites and sugar. Makes 2 pies. Half the ingredients makes one 8-inch pie.

title: grilled corn
directions: Wrap ear of corn with slice of bacon.
Cover back up with shucks, wrap with twine, grill and serve!
Yummy!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, egg, vanilla and baking powder. Slowly add in flour until hard to mix, then stir with spoon.
Cut mixture in 1/2 then roll with rolling pin into 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cutters.
Bake at 400° approximately 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato royale
directions: Mash potatoes or beat with electric beater.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: potato dumplings(serve with sauerbraten, if desired)
directions: Cook potatoes for mashing and cool.
You should have about 3 cups.
Refrigerate 1 hour to chill.
Combine in large bowl mashed potatoes, eggs, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and flour.
Mix well until well combined.
Fill 1/3 cup with mixture.
Remove and form into a ball.
Dredge balls into flour lightly.
Fill wide saucepan with 4-inches lightly salted water and bring to a simmer.
Drop in the potato balls, a few at a time.
When they rise to the surface, cook 5 minutes longer.
Remove with a slotted spoon and keep warm. Makes 12 potato dumpling balls.

title: cake-tomato soup
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, spices and salt. Thoroughly mix Hunt's sauce and soda in small bowl. Add to flour mixture. Stir in eggs, oil, nuts, raisins and fruit juice. Mix well. Pour into greased 10-inch Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes before turning out on serving plate. Dust top with powdered sugar. Makes one 10-inch cake.

title: pink raspberry lemonade mold
directions: Drain raspberries; reserve syrup.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add ice cream by spoonfuls until melted.
Stir in lemonade. Chill in bowl until partially set.
Fold in raspberries and put in lightly greased 6 cup mold.
Chill until firm.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a medium bowl, thoroughly combine meat, egg, cracker or bread crumbs, pepper, salt and vegetables.
Shape into a loaf to fit a 9 x 5 safe
loaf pan so meat does not touch the sides of the dish. Cover with aluminum foil. Put in the oven 40 minutes at 350° and put off the aluminum foil. Put in the oven for 10 minutes more.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in a little oil until well browned on each side.
Remove from oil and drain. Stir into drippings the soup and milk. Cook until blended. Put rice in bottom of baking dish and place pork chops on top.
Pour soup mixture over top of chops. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon bun ring
directions: Butter a Bundt pan (12 cup size).
Sprinkle raisins and chopped nuts.
Arrange frozen dough balls in pan.
Pour on 1/2 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and pudding mix.
Mix 1/4 cup white sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over top.
Cover with foil and leave out overnight.
Do not refrigerate.
Bake next day at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.
Invert on plate after removing from oven.
Serves 8.

title: boiled country ham
directions: Cut off hock, soak ham overnight.
Wash ham and trim off hard surface of cut side of ham.
Fill a large roaster 1/2 full of water.
Put ham in, skin side up.
Start ham at 450° and reduce heat to 300° when water boils.
Cook 20 minutes to the pound or until internal temperature of ham reaches 170°.
When done, allow to cool in liquid for 4 to 5 hours.
Trim the ham of excess fat, leaving 1/4 to 1/2-inches of fat.

title: hand cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Roll dough 3/16-inch thick on lightly floured, cloth covered board.
Place hand lightly on dough.
Trace around hand with pastry wheel.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until no indentation remains when touches, 6 to 8 minutes. Decorate as desired.

title: punch
directions: Mix jello according to directions on package.
Mix frozen orange juice according to directions.
Add sugar, Kool-Aid and pineapple.
Add water to make 2 gallons.
Mix well and serve.

title: onion herb baked bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
The French or Italian bread should be about 16 inches long, halved lengthwise.
In a small bowl, blend all ingredients, except bread.
Generously spread on bread halves. Arrange bread on baking sheet, cut side up.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: bread boat
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and let chill.
Hollow out the bread and fill with the dip.
Cut the bread into cubes and serve with the dip.

title: loaves and fishes country salad(nicoise)
directions: Toss potatoes and beans in salad dressing to coat thoroughly. Season with salt and freshly ground pepper.
Cut garlic clove in half and rub the inside of a salad bowl. Arrange potatoes and beans in the bowl and surround with egg quarters.
Place tuna chunks in the center and decorate with olives and anchovy fillets. Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon rolls
directions: Butter 4 slices of brown bread (crust removed), then cover with 1/4 pound thinly sliced smoked salmon. Sprinkle with lemon juice and freshly ground black pepper. Roll up each slice tightly, pressing together well, then cut each roll crosswise into slices about 1/4-inch thick. Keep in the refrigerator until ready to serve. If desired, the butter may be replaced by cream cheese. Makes about 54.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together.
For hot chocolate, mix 3 tablespoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: easy tea cakes
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, and oil.
Add nuts or chocolate chips.
Spoon batter in small balls onto a cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly.
Reserve 1/4 cup of this mixture.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, milk and egg yolks.
Bring mixture to a good boil, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add the butter and vanilla.
Pour into crust and let cool, then cover with whipped cream (slightly sweetened) and sprinkle reserved 1/4 cup mixture on top.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until tests done and light brown.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Place in loaf pan. Bake 45 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk and follow directions on box.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mix over crackers.
Put a second layer of crackers and remaining pudding mixture.
Put another layer of crackers, then put chocolate icing on crackers.
Chill before serving.

title: stuffed peppers 57
directions: Slice stem ends from peppers and scoop out seeds.
Blanch in boiling salted water 5 minutes. Drain well. Combine ground beef and remaining ingredients. Stuff peppers.
Arrange in greased baking dish. Top with extra 57 sauce, if desired. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until meat is cooked.
Makes 4 servings (3 cups meat mixture).

title: raisin oatmeal muffins
directions: Use 1 yeast cake.
Mix dough according to recipe on yeast cake. Just pinch off piece of dough (about 1/2 cup) and set aside in refrigerator to use next time.
When ready to use it again, boil a medium size potato; slice it up in cup of water.
When tender, mash it up using potato water and all with piece of dough you saved out. Proceed with your bread making but always save out that 1/2 cup of dough for next time.
You never have to buy but one yeast cake this way.
When you take the 1/2 cup of dough out of refrigerator, let set until it reaches room temperature before putting it into mashed potato water.

title: pepper hash
directions: Grind all together.
Pour boiling water over ground peppers and onions.
Let this sit for 15 minutes.
Squeeze thoroughly.

title: lumpia rolls
directions: Brown meat; add soy sauce, Accent, garlic salt, pepper, carrots and onion, cool slightly, then add 1 egg.
Take wrappers, cut into 2 triangles.
Put approximately 1 tablespoon meat mixture onto edge of wrapper and roll, fold ends in when rolled half way. Seal ends with beaten egg.
Pan fry 3 to 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes approximately 100.
This can be frozen before they are fried.

title: pecan chews
directions: Cook 1 cup cream, sugar, salt and syrup to soft ball stage. Add 1 cup cream.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add last cup of cream. Cook to firm ball stage.
Stir often (scorches easily).
Add vanilla and pecans.
Stir to coat.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet and press with hands.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Use for fresh fruit dip.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add seasonings, onion and sour cream.
Stir until it begins to thicken.
Fold into the green beans and pour into greased pan.
Add grated cheese on top.
Melt the 2 tablespoons margarine and add to the Rice Krispies.
Sprinkle over top of bean mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookie dough cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Generously grease bottom and sides of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Combine margarine with cookie crumbs. Press onto bottom and sides of pan.

title: date pudding
directions: Boil together for 3 minutes the chopped dates, hot water and brown sugar.

title: cherry winks cookies
directions: Shape into balls and roll each ball in 2 1/2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Top each cookie with 1/2 cherry. Bake in oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Do not stack or store until cold.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix the brown sugar, mustard and cornstarch in small saucepan. Slowly stir in vinegar.
Add lemon peel, lemon juice, water and raisins; stir over low heat until thickened.
Serve hot over ham slices.
Makes 2 cups.

title: peanut butter sundae sauce
directions: Mix water and sugar together in a small saucepan.
Place on medium heat until it comes to full boil.
Boil for 5 minutes (until thoroughly dissolved).
Let cool for a few minutes.
Add peanut butter to 1/2 cup of sugar and water mixture.
Heat until peanut butter blends with "simple" syrup.
Serve on vanilla ice cream, pancakes, etc.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Stir together lime Jell-O, boiling water and marshmallows until dissolved.
Add pineapple and cottage cheese.
Cool until just beginning to congeal.
Fold in whipped cream, cabbage and mayonnaise.

title: easy chicken thighs
directions: Brown chicken thighs in melted butter.
Add water, bouillon cubes and garlic powder.
Simmer for 45 minutes on low heat.

title: french fancies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Add flour and salt to creamed mixture alternately with milk beating well after each addition.
For each cookie, shape dough around a cherry to form a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 350° 12 - 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Dip cookie tops in glaze.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over cooled pretzels.
Mix next 3 ingredients; mix jello and hot water.
Add frozen strawberries while jello is still hot!! When thickened, layer on cheese and pretzel mixture. Refrigerate.
Best when made the day before.

title: holiday ice cream mold
directions: In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat heavy or whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Reduce mixer speed to low; beat in remaining ingredients just until blended.
Pour into 6 cup mold.
Cover with foil or plastic wrap and freeze until firm. With metal spatula, loosen edges of frozen mixture from mold.
In large bowl or sink of very hot water, dip frozen mixture almost to top to loosen; dry mold with towel.
Invert mixture onto platter. Return to freezer.

title: yummies
directions: Melt
caramels
with milk.
Add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Chill.
Melt candy coating and dip caramels. Drop to set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs and oleo. Place mixture in buttered 9 x 12 pan. Brown crumbs lightly in oleo and sprinkle over casserole. Refrigerate overnight. Remove about one hour before cooking. Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven. Serves 8.

title: hermina's meat loaf
directions: Saute pepper and onion in margarine.
Add to the other ingredients.
Mix some margarine with catsup and brown sugar. Spread on bottom of baking dish.
Put mixed roast on top.
Put catsup on top and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove and let cool approximately 10 minutes.
Run knife around side of meat loaf. Invert on meat platter.
Can garnish with cooked peas which can be put around bottom of meat loaf.
Serves 10.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Wash chicken and place in a baking dish.
Mix together the next 3 ingredients and coat chicken well.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Serve over rice.

title: spoonburger
directions: Saute meat in fat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boiling point, lower heat and cook slowly for 30 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill several hours.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except veggies.
Pour mixture over veggies.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Crumble meat in a large pan, then add all other ingredients. Simmer for 2 or 3 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Stir well.
Pour half into a greased 10-inch iron skillet.
Top with cheese.
Add remaining corn meal mixture.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix ham, cheese, margarine, onion and Worcestershire sauce together well.
Split rolls and spread mixture on bottom half. Top with other half and wrap in foil.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Can be frozen and heated when needed.
Makes 60 delights.

title: spinach delight
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Beat eggs, add spinach and melted butter, salt, pepper and flour.
Add all cheeses and stir.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in oven or microwave.
Scoop out potato from shell into mixing bowl.
Mash potatoes with milk and margarine or butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon mashed potatoes back into shells and place in oven under boiler until tops begin to brown, approximately 5 minutes.
Shredded cheese, bacon bits, sour cream or other ingredients may be added to mashed potato mix before broiling, if desired.

title: egg casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine eggs, milk, mustard, salt and cheese.
Beat well.
Pour over bread and meat in pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: don's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Blend oleo, sugar and syrup together.
Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange pineapple and cherries on the syrup mixture and heat in oven 15 minutes.
Mix cake according to package directions.
