(I use the pineapple juice for the liquid). After 15 minutes, remove pan from oven and pour cake batter on slowly.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes, until cake is done.
Invert immediately.

title: mandarin orange bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased pan 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Cook carrots in just enough water to cover.
Save cooking water.
Chop carrots.
Add onion, cheese, crackers and pepper.
Mix together.
Add small amount of reserved water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or microwave on High for 5 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Beat slightly eggs with salt and milk.
Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix sausage, egg mixture, and bread with mustard and cheese.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, cover and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together sausage, cheese and Bisquick (like you would shortening and flour for a pie crust).
Mix together.
Drop from spoon on baking sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sneaky petes
directions: Mix in blender orange juice, lemonade, sugar and some 7-Up into the juice mixture.
Pour in large bowl.
Add rest of 7-Up, cranberry juice and vodka or gin.
Mix and then pour into large plastic container with cover.
Place in refrigerator for at least 12 hours.
Pour 7-Up or ginger ale over mixture.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish with enough broth to cover the meat.
Brown the Rice-A-Roni in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add the seasoning and evaporated milk.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zimtsterne(cinnamon stars)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually beat in 2 cups powdered sugar.
Reserve 3/4 cup of mixture.
To the remainder, add rind, cinnamon and almonds, blending well.
Work in about 1/2 cup more of the sugar to make smooth.
Dust board or wax paper with some of the remaining sugar.
Pat out 1/3 cup dough at a time.
Coat top with powdered sugar.
Cover with wax paper and roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with floured star cutter on well-greased cookie sheet and let dry for 2 to 3 hours.
Dough may be dropped by teaspoon on well-greased cookie sheet and allowed to dry as before. Top each cookie, rolled or dropped, with reserved egg mixture and bake at 300°.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: atlanta pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Remove chops and cook celery.
Drain grease and add tomato sauce, rice, celery and chops.
Simmer 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Season with garlic salt, if desired.

title: chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round cake pans.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually add 1/2 cup of the sugar. Beat until stiff and glossy.
Sift remaining sugar, flour, soda and salt into another bowl.
Pour in oil and half of buttermilk. Beat 1 minute.
Add remaining buttermilk, egg yolks and chocolate. Beat 1 minute more.
Fold in meringue.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.
Frost with following icing.

title: banana bread
directions: Break eggs into mixing bowl and beat until well blended.
Cut bananas in 1-inch pieces into bowl with eggs.
Mash with fork and mix with eggs.

title: mississippi spice muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix in applesauce and spices.
Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Add to applesauce mixture and beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in lightly greased mini muffin pans at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Batter keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.
Baked muffins freeze well.

title: sweet relish
directions: Grind together cucumbers, onions and peppers, then add 1 handful of salt.
Let set overnight.
Drain and add the rest of ingredients.
Cook slowly 1/2 hour.
Put in jars and seal.
Yields about 15 to 20 pints.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make a batter of flour, 2 cups of sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter in pan and top with peaches and juice.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and cook until thickened. Add strawberry jello.
Cool slightly.
Pour over strawberries. Place in baked pie shells.
Chill overnight and top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken enchiladas ole
directions: Combine chicken, 1 cup sour cream, 3/4 cup cheese and onion; mix well.
Dip tortillas in hot oil to soften; drain.
Top each tortilla with 1/4 cup chicken mixture.
Roll up tightly.
Place seam side down in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with salsa.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
As soon as they come from the oven, sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Serve with remaining sour cream.
Makes 6 servings.
Great way to use up leftover chicken.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients with oil.
Pour over crackers.
Let stand 1 hour.
Mix in large container.

title: three layer jello salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let jell overnight.
Add layer of Cool Whip or Dream Whip.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Spread on top of Cool Whip layer.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: buttermilk scones
directions: *For new twist, substitute other types of dried fruits for the currants.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar. Add oil, nuts, egg and vanilla. Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to mixture.
Put in a greased 8 x
8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until it shrinks from edge of pan.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake according to instructions.
When removed from oven, spread pineapple, juice and all, over top of cake.
Let cool.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients as for pie dough.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in bottom of rectangular pan.
Cover with cherry pie filling.
Spread rest of oat mixture on top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar, chocolate pudding mix and sour cream. Add all other ingredients except the confectioners sugar and whip cream.

Add chips last. Beat with a mixer 2 to 3 minutes THEN STIR IN THE CHIPS. Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done in center. Let cool 30 minutes before removing from pan. Sprinkle with sugar and/or serve with whip cream. Very moist. Very good.

title: best ever fudge
directions: Melt the Velveeta cheese and oleo in a double boiler, stir occasionally.
In the meantime, put the powdered sugar, cocoa and pecans in a very large bowl.
(I use a large blue enameled pan with white dots on it, the same one I roast a turkey in.)
Mix well. When cheese and oleo have melted, stir in vanilla and immediately pour over mixture in large pan.
You have to work quickly mixing this, and it is very hard to mix (you cannot use a mixer).
Either line your cookie sheets with waxed paper or spray with Pam.
You have to pat the fudge into the pans.
It makes a very large amount, but it can easily be halved.

title: green rice ring
directions: Saute onions, minced garlic and parsley in oleo. Beat eggs and add milk and other ingredients.
Bake in well-greased and floured ring mold at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Do not brown!
Remove on plate and serve hot.

title: vegetable layered salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in salad bowl.
Use just enough salad dressing to cover last layer and seal in moisture.
Let stand overnight covered in refrigerator.
Just before serving, sprinkle with grated cheese and bacon bits.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and chilies.
Drain off liquid.
Mix stewed tomatoes, beans and corn, all undrained, with meat.
Add taco seasoning, salad dressing mix and water.
Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend together.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken with biscuits
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine soup, chicken and cheese.
Cook over medium heat until cheese melts and mixture is hot, stirring occasionally.
To serve, spoon chicken mixture into 3 bowls.
Top with biscuits.
Makes 3 servings.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit and arrange in a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine butter, sugar and curry powder. Bring to a boil. Pour over fruit. Garnish with cherries.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain well.
Place all beans in a casserole dish and add browned meat.
Add brown sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar and catsup.
Mix well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: golden creme of potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onions, parsley, salt and bouillon cube.
Bring to boil.
Cover; simmer until vegetables are tender.
Gradually add milk to flour.
Add vegetables, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Tear bread into pieces.
Combine bread and milk in a small bowl and squeeze into a soft pulp.
In a large bowl, combine beef, bread and milk mixture, eggs, sausages, Parmesan cheese, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into a large loaf about 10 inches long x 3 inches thick.
Coat meat loaf with bread crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until golden. Add wine.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Add tomatoes.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes longer, basting with sauce a few times during cooking. Cool 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.
Serve with a few tablespoons of sauce over meat loaf.
It's wonderfully moist.
Throw a few carrots in the pan while cooking for a veggie.

title: hubbard seafood salad
directions: Cook shrimp and scallops; cool.
Make salad dressing.
Mix vinegar, oil, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Line platter with lettuce.
Add chopped tomatoes, avocado, onion and seafood.
Toss with salad dressing.
Arrange crabmeat over all.

title: fudgy toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Press firmly into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix ground beef, onion, salt, pepper and green onions.
Brown mixture together and add broccoli or spinach, mushrooms and 1/2 can of cream of mushroom soup.
Cook bacon in oven.
Place bacon on paper towel to drain.
In separate bowl, mix eggs and milk together.
Now put the ground beef mixture in pie crust.
You can put sausage on top or bottom.
Cheese can also be layered on the top or bottom.
Place bacon slices on top now and pour egg and milk mixture over the top.
Cook in oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except onion rings.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover; bake for 55 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove cover. Add the frozen onion rings; bake 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Trim all visible fat from steak; cut steak into bite-size pieces.
Cook in hot oil in a large skillet over medium heat until browned, stirring often.
Add onion and green pepper; cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in tomatoes and next 4 ingredients. Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and cook 45 minutes or until tender, adding additional water, if necessary.
Serve over rice. Yield: 4 servings (341 calories (22% from fat) per 3/4 cup meat mixture and 1/2 cup rice).

title: best than ever cake
directions: Mix
cake mix, pudding, sour cream, oil, water and eggs for at least two minutes.	Fold in chips, grated chocolate and pecans. Bake
in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Alternate layer of potatoes, green pepper and onions in baking dish. Season each layer with salt and pepper. Mix soup and milk. Pour over potatoes. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together.
Cream shortening.
Add sugars gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, oats and coconut; mix well.
Shape dough in small balls and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in a moderate (375°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute the onion and green pepper or green chilies in the margarine.
Mix together the remaining ingredients, except the sour cream and cheese.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the corn mixture, sauteed onion mixture, sour cream (or yogurt) and 2 cups cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ice cream surprise
directions: Unwrap and place 5 to 6 ice cream sandwiches in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix flavorings with defrosted Cool Whip. Spread layer of ice cream sandwiches with Cool Whip mixture, then repeat layers.
Toast almonds (lightly) and sprinkle on top. Freeze.
Cut into squares and serve.
Serves 20 to 24 small servings.

title: swiss steak
directions: Dredge steak in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in hot oil. Add onion, celery, garlic, chili sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender.

title: mints
directions: Mix with fork the cheese, flavoring and coloring.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix with hands until mixture is like a ball of clay. Pinch off small balls.
Roll in sugar.
Press in mold.

title: carrie's favorite blue cheese dressing
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix together cream cheese, Blue cheese, mayonnaise and Worcestershire.
Slowly add half and half.
Mixture will be thin but will thicken when chilled.

title: baked fish
directions: Cut thawed fish into serving size pieces.
Coat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Arrange in single layer in baking pan.
Pour milk over and bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°. Toast bread crumbs lightly in frying pan.
Add parsley to sour cream and mix.
Spoon sour cream mixture and bread crumbs over fish and bake at 350° for 10 minutes and then serve.

title: dale's chewie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the margarine with the light brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in the vanilla.
Stir in the flour and then add the pecans.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake in the preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Cake will sink slightly in the center.
Cool thoroughly on a rack, then cut into brownie like squares.
Recipe yields about 35 squares.

title: tamale pie
directions: Stir cornmeal and salt into boiling water in top of double boiler.
Cook, stirring, until mixture begins to thicken.
Add milk, place over hot water, cover and cook 30 minutes.
Fry beef and onion until done; add chili, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Line bottom and sides of 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole, which has been greased, with 3/4 of hot mush.
Pour in meat and tomato filling. Cover with remaining mush.
Can top with Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add tomatoes.
Fill can twice with water.
Add all ingredients except orzo.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add orzo.
Cook 15 more minutes.

title: microwave ritz pizza
directions: First, cut up a hot dog into small round pieces.

Then take the crackers and squirt a little bit of ketchup and mustard on them. Next, take the hot dog pieces and put them on the crackers. Finally, put a little piece of cheese over it and pop it in the microwave for 30 seconds.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Serve by filling coffee mug with 1/3 to 1/2 of mixture.
Add boiling water.
Top off with mini marshmallows.
Store in airtight container for freshness.

title: hash brown casserole with jalapeno
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz, soup, sour cream, onion and butter together in big bowl.
Stir in hash browns (frozen).
Pour all into 11 x 14-inch greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs (browned in butter).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cranberry fizz
directions: In a large non-metal pitcher or punch bowl, combine cranberry juice cocktail, grapefruit juice, orange juice and sugar.
Just before serving, add ginger ale, stirring gently.
Makes 16 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: In heavy medium saucepan, combine unflavored gelatine, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in condensed milk and eggs.
Mix well; let stand 1 minute.
Over low heat, cook and stir about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pumpkin; mix well. Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Makes 1 pie.

title: italian sausage bread
directions: Thaw dough.
Cook sausages thoroughly; drain and split in half lengthwise.
Saute onion until tender.
On floured board, roll dough out to 15 x 9 inch rectangle.
Fold 1/3 of dough over middle to make 10 x 9 inch rectangle.
Arrange sausage on folded dough. Spread onions and spaghetti sauce on sausage.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Fold remaining 1/3 of dough over sausage filling; seal all edges tightly.
Place on greased sheet pan. Brush dough with melted butter; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let rise 50 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Slice and serve.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook all to a boil; simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Slowly pour hot mixture into 2 slightly beaten eggs. Beat vigorously.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix.
Pour over cauliflower as a dressing.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Fold in with the fruit mixture.
Could use Cool Whip, but tastes best with the whipped cream.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour.
Cook slowly until mixture thickens.
Let cool.
Stir about 1 teaspoon Fruit-Fresh into bananas, to keep them from turning dark.
Spread bananas in bottom of pie shell.
Top with a layer of coconut, then a layer of nuts. Pour cooled filling over the nuts and top with 1 large container Cool Whip.
Makes 2 (8-inch) pies.

title: easy round steak
directions: In skillet, brown meat; cut in strips and put in oil.
Salt and pepper.
Remove from skillet.
Add other ingredients in skillet and stir until mixed well.
Add 1 1/2 soup cans of water.
Put meat in casserole dish.
Pour mixture in skillet over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Bake, covered.
You may need to add more water if it cooks down.

title: pickled watermelon rind *
directions: Peel rind and cut in medium thin slices.
Soak overnight in a weak brine made of 2 tablespoons salt and 1 quart of water. Drain and cook rind in fresh water until tender.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Add rind and cook until clear.
Pack in hot, sterile jars, fill with syrup; seal.

title: quick holiday fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together in large bowl.
Add pecan pieces, coconut and marshmallows to your taste.
Slowly blend in Cool Whip until mixed thoroughly.

title: nanny's cheese biscuits
directions: Grate cheese; let oleo get to room temperature.
Mix together thoroughly; roll into large rolls.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Pour over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine meats, bread crumbs and seasoning. Beat eggs slightly; add milk. Mix together and put in loaf pan.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: *If using self-rising flour omit baking soda and salt.

title: sugar-free chocolate ice cream pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until center of pie is firm.
Cool.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: copper pennies salad
directions: Cut carrots in rounds. Cook until tender. Do not overcook. While still hot, add all other ingredients with carrots. Mix. Let stand overnight. Keep covered tightly. Refrigerate. Will keep 2 to 3 weeks.

title: baked salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.

title: bacon and horseradish dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with 1 tablespoon sugar, garlic powder and onion powder to taste. Chill for about an hour. Garnish with crumbled bacon. Serve with ripple chips.

title: fritters
directions: Add any kind of fruit or corn.
Fry like pancakes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Stir together.
Sauce is good for chicken, ribs or anything you wish to use it for.

title: red chile onion rings
directions: Soak onions in milk in a large bowl for one hour.
Drain well. Mix flour, chile powder, cornstarch, salt, cumin, sugar and paprika in another large bowl.
Dredge onions in flour mixture; shake off excess.
Heat oil in large heavy saucepan to 360°.
Add onions in batches and cook until golden brown, about 45 seconds. Transfer to paper towels using a slotted spoon; drain well.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Stir up and put in container and then freeze.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix vegetable oil, melted butter, and Worcestershire sauce. Drizzle butter mixture over cereal, salt, stir and repeat.
Bake at 200 degrees and stir every 20 minutes until crispy.

title: grizzlenuckles
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except powdered sugar (reserve for later).
Press into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
After baking, spread powdered sugar on warm cookies and cut into small squares.
Makes approximately 36 squares.

title: low-fat roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash the potatoes and cut into large chunks.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain off excess grease.
Combine cream of mushroom, cream of chicken and cream of celery soup with 1 cup of milk.
Add this to sausage.
Then add onion, bell pepper and rice. Mix well.
Add salt and black pepper to taste.
Bake in casserole dish in 350° oven for 1 hour.
This makes a large casserole.

title: ambrosia(salad or dessert)
directions: Whip cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Add all other ingredients.
Best if made and refrigerated one night before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix condensed milk and cream cheese 5 minutes with electric mixer.
Strain all fruits to take off liquids.
Mix condensed milk and cream cheese mixture with the fruits and refrigerate.

title: easy salad
directions: Drain the first 4 ingredients. After veggies have drained, place in large bowl. Add enough mayonnaise only to coat. Add small amount of Ranch dressing, just enough to cut taste of mayonnaise, at least 1 tablespoon. Best to add grated cheese an hour or so before serving salad, but can be added at any time. Refrigerate.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Combine all ingredients except dough.
Mix well.
Roll dough out in squares.
Put 2 tablespoons mix in each piece of dough. Fry in deep fat.

title: fudge(no cook peanut butter)
directions: In top of double boiler, melt the butter and peanut butter together.
Add in the corn syrup, water and vanilla, then blend in the dry ingredients until creamy and smooth.
Spread in a generously buttered pan.
Chill for 2 hours until firm.

title: easy barbecued chicken
directions: Cook chicken (boil).
Remove from water and dice.
Put diced chicken in slow cooker and cover with barbecue sauce.
Heat a couple of hours (or all day on lower temperature).

title: never fail pecan divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup in a heavy boiler (double boiler). Bring to a boil and cook until mixture spins a thread.
Pour half of the syrup mixture over the egg whites and begin stirring.
Cook remaining half until it forms a hard ball (crack stage).
Pour this into the egg-syrup mixture.
Add vanilla and continue to stir until it holds its shape.
Add pecans and drop onto wax paper.

title: gingerbread man or ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Stir in molasses. Add 1 1/4 cups flour sifted with soda, salt and spices.
Stir thoroughly.
Add remaining flour alternately with milk and vinegar (mixed).
Chill dough.
Roll about 1/3-inch thick on floured board.
Use ginger boy cutter.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 26 boys.

title: fast chicken pot pie
directions: Place cooked and diced chicken in baking dish (9 x 13-inches). Pour mixed vegetables over chicken. Pour soup over vegetables. Combine milk, melted margarine and flour; pour over soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Cream well.
Add flour, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add apples and 1/2 pecans.
Pour batter into greased tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle remaining pecans over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook vegetables in microwave and drain. Add the other ingredients, then 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add to the first pie shell and cover with the second one.
Bake until it begins to bubble, about 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 225° and bake until brown.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Scald the milk.
Stir in butter, sugar and salt.
Cool until lukewarm.
Stir in yeast, eggs and flour.
Knead until a smooth dough is formed.
Place in a greased bowl and cover.
Let rise until double.
Divide dough in three parts.
Roll in 10-inch circles.
Cut into 12 wedges.
Shape pieces.
Roll up each piece from the wide end to the point.
Place on a greased baking sheet and pull ends inward to make a crescent. Let rise until double.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Whip softened cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and blend well. Add pineapple, nuts and cherries. Add Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Break up the chocolate and put it in a heatproof bowl.
Stand the bowl in a pan of boiling water.
Stir the chocolate until it melts, then leave it to cool. Fold it into the yogurt.

title: venison and beef barbecue
directions: Clean doves thoroughly.
Place in large saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to boil over full gas flame; reduce flame to simmer (200° to 225° dial setting on controlled burner) and cook until doves are just tender.
Remove doves and place in shallow baking dish or pan.
Thicken stock with paste of flour and water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place cooked doves in shallow baking dish or pan.
Cover with thickened gravy.
Top with pastry.
Bake in moderate gas oven (375°) for 1 hour or until crust is brown.
Allow 2 doves per serving.

title: fruit cake (uncooked)
directions: Chop fruit and nuts.
Add marshmallows and blend by hand.
Add Eagle Brand; blend further.
Add crumbs a cup at a time.
When well blended, shape into four rolls and wrap in foil.
Store in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.
Slice and serve.
Refrigerate remainder.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and slowly add sour cream.
Mix together. Add all other ingredients and mix well.
May make ahead and refrigerate to improve flavor.

title: hot apple punch
directions: Combine ingredients in large stock pot.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix butter in large casserole dish.
In another bowl, mix flour, sugar and milk.
Mix well and pour over butter.
Then pour a large can of peach slices and syrup on top.
Bake at 400° until the top is well browned.

title: tomato pie
directions: Grease pie plate well with shortening.
Press biscuits in plate to make a crust.

title: roquefort cheese dressing
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Let age for about 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: lillian's "preacher pleaser"
directions: Mix jello and sugar in a large bowl before adding water. Dissolve completely.
Add apple juice; chill until partially jelled.
Remove and mix with electric mixer until it foams to top of bowl.
Add crushed pineapple, fruit cocktail and Cool Whip. Stir in nuts and marshmallows.
Garnish with marshmallows, let set until congealed.

title: molded cranberry gelatin
directions: Spray mold.
Sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup orange juice.
Cook over low heat 2 to 3 minutes, until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups orange juice and cranberry sauce until well combined.
Pour into mold and chill 24 hours.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine meat and seasonings. Form into balls and saute in oil until brown.
Drain.
Add chili sauce and jelly.
Simmer slowly, covered, for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Fry the bacon.
In the bacon drippings, fry the pieces of loaf bread.
Add stewed tomatoes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Crumble bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Good to serve with vegetables.

title: icebox gingerbread mini muffins
directions: Cream 1 1/4 cups margarine or Crisco and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs.

Mix and add to creamed mixture the 1/2 cup Grandma molasses, 1 cut buttermilk, 4 cups plain flour, 2 teaspoons soda, 1/2 cup pecans (chopped fine), 1/2 cup raisins, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon allspice and 2 teaspoons ginger.
Cover bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Can keep 1 or 2 weeks.
Drop by teaspoon. Never stir down.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: no cook sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and put in salt water; when whole egg will float in water, it has enough salt.
Soak 6 to 7 days. Drain saltwater and rinse; slice.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in roasting pan; add onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over spareribs.
Cover lightly and cook in moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and roast 20 minutes longer.
Serve with cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: french beans supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients except the green beans.
Heat the beans and drain.
Spread the sauce over the beans and serve.

title: spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach; wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry. Tear leaves into bite-size pieces and combine with oranges and onion rings.
Toss with dressing; serve immediately.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: white sugar cake cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs and other ingredients.
Drop from spoon onto greased pan.
Bake at 275° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: oven barbecued spareribs
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients except ribs.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Broil ribs 45 minutes at 350°.
Put broiled ribs in baking dish.
Cover with sauce.
Cover with tin foil.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours or more.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Whip cream cheese.
Add pineapple, pepper, onions, salt and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Chill for 2 hours.
Form into a ball and roll in the rest of the nuts.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Combine all ingredients and place in oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet cherry-nut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a mold or dish. Chill. Enjoy!!

title: fall apple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in apple juice and add other ingredients. When it begins to set, add chopped red apples with peeling left on. Add chopped celery and pecans.
Chill.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.

title: campbell's classic glorified chicken(an easy way to make the most of chicken since 1957)
directions: Oven:
In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, arrange chicken, skin side up and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Spoon soup over chicken.
Bake 20 minutes more or until chicken is fork-tender.
Stir sauce before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: modeling dough
directions: Mix all together very well.
Mixture should be stiff.
Knead together thoroughly.
Will keep for week in a covered jar in the refrigerator.

title: spinach dip
directions: In bowl, blend vegetable soup, sour cream, water chestnuts, mayonnaise and spinach (thaw and squeeze all water from spinach before mixing with other ingredients).
Chill for 2 hours or overnight.

title: chocolate nut drop cookies
directions: Cream the butter, then add the sifted brown sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add the well beaten eggs. Cream.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add with milk alternately; mix until smooth.
Add melted chocolate, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Fold into mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on oiled baking sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients but the ginger ale.
Mix in ginger ale just before serving.

title: greek-style potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; cool slightly and combine with the slivered olives.
In a small pan of boiling water, boil garlic for 5 minutes, then peel garlic cloves.
In a blender, puree red wine vinegar, garlic cloves, olive oil, oregano, parsley and pepper. Pour dressing over warm potatoes.
Add Feta cheese, toss and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon-blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of 12 muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Beat eggs slightly in a medium bowl with a fork.
Mix in baking mix, sugar, vegetable oil and yogurt just until moistened (batter should be lumpy).
Gently fold blueberries into batter and fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes, or until golden brown.
Carefully remove muffins from pan right away.
Cool on wire rack.

title: caramel pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Halve mixture and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Toast in oven until golden brown the margarine, almonds and coconut. Divide mixture and sprinkle over pies.
Drizzle the caramel ice cream topping over this. Refrigerate. (This pie also freezes well.)

title: chicken and potato casserole
directions: Mix soups and add 2 cups of milk.
Pour 1/4 into bottom of pan.
Layer chicken, 1/2 onion and thin slices of potatoes. Repeat layering and bake in 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
You may top with grated cheese.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese, mustard, olives, onions, mayonnaise, horseradish spread, paprika, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco; mix well.
Spread on slice of ham.
Place a square of cheese on top of cheese mixture.
Roll up.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut rye bread with small round cutter.
Slice ham into 10 slices.
Place on top of bread.
Freezes well.

title: double-chocolate caramel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour 12-c. bundt pan. Make cake batter as directed on package-except stir in chips. Pour into pan.

title: cheese sandwich pie
directions: Mix egg, flour, salt, pepper and half the milk.
Beat.
Add remaining milk and oregano.
Beat well.
Stir in 1/2 of cheese (shredded) and all of pepperoni.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Put remaining cheese on top. Bake until melted, approximately 2 minutes.
Cut in 24 wedges. Serve warm.

title: onion baked chicken
directions: Combine soup mix with bread; dip chicken in water, then in bread crumb mixture, coating well.
Place in shallow baking dish and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: smacking good brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour in greased pan and bake in oven for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: strawberry icebox treat
directions: At room temperature, cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Mix remaining ingredients, then freeze.
Use a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: lumpia shanghai
directions: In a bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Season with salt, pepper and ajinomoto.
Blend in egg and soy sauce.
Beat mixture thoroughly.
At one end of a lumpia wrapper, spoon about 2 tablespoons of the pork mixture and roll tightly.
Brush end of wrapper with water to seal. Cut rolls into 2-inch pieces.
Deep fat fry.

title: reuben dip
directions: Chop corned beef and add all to a slow cooker. Let heat through. Serve with little squares of rye bread.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Layer in glass bowl with strawberries and vanilla wafers.
Let sit overnight.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Bring tomato and next seven ingredients to a boil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat. Reduce heat and simmer uncovered, 30 minutes or until thickened. Spoon hot mixture in hot sterilized jars, filling to 1/4-inch from top. Remove bubbles. Wipe jars and screw on bands. Process in boiling water bath.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in large rectangular glass dish as given in order.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together the next 5 ingredients.
Add the sifted ingredients to the egg mixture. Add the apples and nuts.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes in a greased 8 x 12-inch pan at 350°.

title: east pralines
directions: Mix first five ingredients; cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Add pecans; boil 2 to 5 minutes or until soft ball stage.
Beat until shiny; drop on wax paper to cool.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients.
Heat on stove and pour over vegetables.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: barbecue sauce for grilling chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients until hot.
Brush on chicken upon turning on grill.
Makes enough for 2 chickens.

title: personal pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Split English muffins and put them on cookie sheet.
Mix tomato sauce, basil and oregano.
Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons mixture evenly on muffin halves.
Bake in oven until the cheese melts, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: charlie's texas chili
directions: Marinate beef for a few hours in beer and then drain.
Brown beef in hot shortening.
Add peppers, onions, tomatoes, tomato sauce and beans.
Cook 1 hour.
Add spices.
Cook 2 more hours.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together and store in refrigerator.
Use 1/4 cup of mix to 1 cup of hot water.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Add fruit and mix.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts, or one large casserole dish lined with graham cracker crumbs.

title: horseradish dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate for flavors to mix.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, brown and white sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together and add the flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and chopped nuts.
Drop by ice cream scoop (flatten slightly) on ungreased cookie sheet.
You may roll in sugar before baking.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 15 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl except the hashbrowns. In a 9x13 inch cake pan, sprinkle half the bag of hashbrowns on the bottom of the pan.
Pour over the hashbrowns the bowl of mixed ingredients and top with the remaining hashbrowns.
Cook for 45-55 minutes on 350 degrees (or according to hashbrown package).
For extra cheesy flavor, I usually sprinkle cheese on the top.

title: chocolate crumble bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly on top and return to oven for 3 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Blend pineapple juice, sugar, flour, vinegar and beaten egg in saucepan.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Cool completely.
Fold in Cool Whip, pineapple, peanuts and apples.
Chill.
Serves 10.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 2 (9-inch) graham cracker crusts.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Chill and serve. This can be made fat free by using nonfat cream cheese and egg whites.

title: snickers cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to peanut butter mixture.

Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Take 1 tablespoon of dough and flatten into a round shape in the palm of your hand.	Place Snickers bar in center and fold dough around it.	Roll in palms of your hands to form a smooth ball with the Snickers bar totally covered with the dough.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and place on a wire rack to cool.
Drizzle melted chocolate on top of cookie.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the butter, sugar and chopped pecans.
Place crackers on cookie sheet.
Pour boiling ingredients over cookies. Bake for about 10 minutes in a 400° oven.
Makes 24 cookies.
Very good!

title: lasagna superb
directions: In large
frying
pan,
saute
onion in oil until soft; add Italian
sausage
and
beef
and garlic and cook, stirring until meat is browned.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste and 1 cup water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, oregano, pepper and sugar, stirring until mixed.
Cover pan and simmer about 1 1/2 hours, if
you want fully developed flavor.
Meanwhile, cook noodles in
salted boiling
water
as
package directs, until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain,
rinse
in cold water, drain again. Arrange 1/2 of
noodles
in
bottom
of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layers of Ricotta cheese, Cheddar cheese and 1/2 of the sauce. Layer the other 1/2 noodles, Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 sauce. Top with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix butter and cheese.
Add flour and Tabasco sauce.
Roll into small balls.
Chill 24 hours.
Bake on a floured sheet at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
These may be kept in refrigerator for several days before baking.

title: reta's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with salt, pepper and margarine until done; drain and dice or slice.
Cook broccoli according to directions on package and drain.
Put in dish with chicken.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Puff Pastry: In a saucepan over medium heat, bring water and butter to a boil. Add flour all at once; stir until a smooth ball forms.

Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat until smooth. Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until puffed and golden brown. Cool completely.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture. Pour into prepared crust.
Freeze until firm.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add taco seasoning and water; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine sugar, spices and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans.
When starts to thicken, dump onto wax paper and separate.
Store in covered container.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain and combine vegetables.
Toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat. Stir occasionally.
Pour over vegetables.
Stir gently to blend. Cover and chill at least 24 hours.
Drain excess liquid before serving.

title: pecan-sage stuffing
directions: Combine bread cubes with sage and pecans.
Beat eggs with milk and add melted butter.
Lightly toss liquid with bread mixture. Turn into a lightly greased casserole.
Bake covered at 400° for 30 minutes and uncovered an additional 10 minutes to brown.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Dough will be stiff.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and pinch dough in half.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick, about the size of a dinner plate.
Spread with butter and cut into pie shape sections (8).
Roll crescent style and place on baking sheet.
Let rise about 1 hour and bake at 450° until brown, 10 to 12 minutes. Brush with melted butter after removing from oven.

title: fruit pudding salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix juice with pudding.
To this, add Cool Whip, pineapple, mandarin oranges, marshmallows and other fruit if you desire.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Combine cake mix, oil and eggs; beat thoroughly.
Stir in oranges with their juice.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then out on racks.

title: wild rice and sausage casserole
directions: Put rice and consomme in a casserole dish and bake until the consomme is absorbed, about 1 hour.
Brown beef.
Put aside. Brown sausage; drain off fat.
Mix ground beef, sausage, mushrooms and pepper to taste.
Add meat mixture to the rice mixture, stirring thoroughly.
Bake at 350° until completely heated.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in a Crisco-coated 6 x 10-inch baking pan. Sprinkle cornstarch over fruit.
Combine sugar, salt and peach juice.
Pour over peaches.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Boil sugar, milk and oleo until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add raisins, coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Frost cake.

title: south american pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco. Add eggs one at a time, next, add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour. Pour into tube pan and bake at 325° for one hour and twenty minutes. DO NOT OPEN OVEN DOOR WHILE COOKING.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil noodles as package directs.
Brown hamburger, then drain. In very large bowl, combine hamburger, noodles and both jars of sauce.
Pour into 2 casserole dishes and cover each with a package of cheese and pepperoni.
One may be frozen for later.
(Can add cheese and pepperoni later.) Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes. Should be bubbling when done.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Put bread in bottom of a 6 1/2 x 10-inch dish.
Cover with tomatoes. Sprinkle sugar on tomatoes. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle black pepper over all. Bake in oven until brown at 500°.

title: a little chocolate death
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions.
Cool.
Make mousse according to directions; place in fridge 3/4 to 1 hour to cool and set up.
Break brownies in a glass bowl.
Layer mousse, then Cool Whip.
Keep layering; end with Cool Whip.
Break candy on top of last layer.
Sit back and watch the oohs and aahs!

title: chocolate-chip mandel bread
directions: In large bowl, mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla and mix well.
Add walnuts and chips. Mixture should be very thick and sticky.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all to boil; simmer 1/2 hour.

title: party punch
directions: Combine Hi-C concentrate with lemonade and water.
Chill.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Place all ingredients in mixer bowl and beat on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a well-greased 10-inch pie plate or two 8-inch pie plates.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge of pie comes out clean.

title: carrot coconut cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix together sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture, alternating with carrots, about 1/3 at a time.
Stir in coconut. Pour into cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except jello.
Cook until thick.
Add jello.
Cool.
Add strawberries and pour into pie shell.
Place in refrigerator until set.
Cover with whipped topping and garnish with additional strawberries.
Regular or graham cracker crust can be used.

title: pickled cucumber and onions
directions: In a glass bowl or crock, layer cucumber and onions.
In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard, celery seed, and turmeric.
Bring to a boil; stir until sugar dissolves. Pour over cucumber and onions.
Cool.
Cover tight.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Store in refrigerator for up to a month.

title: cornbread deluxe(this is almost a cake.)
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Add cornbread mix.
Bake as directed on the mix package (may take longer; bake until top is brown).

title: ribs
directions: Cook ribs in oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Drain oil.
Add sauce. Cook with sauce for 1 hour.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix seasoned salt, flour and oregano leaves. Blend thoroughly. Moisten chicken by dipping in milk. Coat moistened chicken with flour mixture. Place coated chicken into baking dish sprayed with Pam cooking spray. Drizzle chicken with melted butter. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: hot baked potato salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, mustard, salt, sugar and pepper in small bowl; set aside.
In casserole dish, layer 1/2 potatoes, 1/2 eggs, 1/2 onions and 1/2 of mixture.
Do this 2 times.
Top with bacon crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned cullers
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add milk.
Sift remaining ingredients together, then add this mixture to the sugar, Mazola oil, eggs and milk.
Knead like bread dough.
Roll on floured board 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in pieces about 3 1/2 inches long and 2 1/2 inches wide.
Then cut through this twice with a knife.
Drop in hot shortening and brown lightly, then brown other side. Remove and drain on paper towels.

title: one pot dinner #2
directions: Combine all ingredients in pot.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes until cooked through.

title: pumpkin chiffon
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter. Press into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Combine cream cheese, eggs and 3/4 cup sugar; beat until fluffy.
Spread over crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: oatmeal praline cake
directions: In a small pan, bring water to a boil. Take off heat and add oatmeal.
Let stand and cool.
Mix together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and soda.
Set aside.
Cream together margarine and white and brown sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: sweet potato french fries
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and cut into strips for fries.
Place in water and salt so as not to blacken.
Heat oil in fryer.
When grease is hot enough, shake potatoes in a sealable bowl with flour and salt just to coat the fries.
Shake off excess flour and place into hot grease.
Fry until golden brown and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serve with catsup.
They're a very sweet tasting fry.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Spread 1/2 cracker crumbs in buttered baking dish.
Cover with oysters.
Sprinkle pepper; pour 1/2 cream over casserole.
Add remaining cream and butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef fajitas
directions: Place steak, onion and red pepper into large shallow dish. Combine garlic, lime juice, olive oil, vinegar, cilantro, cumin and salt.
Pour marinade over steak and vegetables.
Toss until coated.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Preheat broiler. Place steak on lined broiler pan.
Broil 8 to 10 minutes on one side.
Turn and add onion, red pepper and rest of marinade.
Broil another 10 minutes or until done.
Cut meat on 45° angle into thin slices.
Divide along with vegetables into tortillas; fold and serve.

title: pineapple nut salad
directions: Thicken pineapple juice with cornstarch, sugar and vanilla. Cool completely; add pineapple, marshmallows, bananas and nuts. Chill; serve.

title: butterscotch lush
directions: Mix together butter, flour and nuts.
Press in to 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: irish tea scone
directions: Boil raisins for 1 minute.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add to floured pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour until brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix above ingredients together and make loaf.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit; do not drain.
Add dry pudding mixes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Mix together boiling water and jello.
Chill Carnation milk and beat until milk stands in peaks, then mix everything together with beater, except graham cracker crumbs.
Line graham cracker crumbs on bottom of a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch dish.
Pour ingredients on top.
Sprinkle a few graham cracker crumbs on top.
Chill until well set.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 the nuts.
Roll into a ball. After refrigerating 1/2 hour, roll ball into the leftover nuts.

title: cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: Slowly add milk to soup, stirring well, until evenly blended. In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternating layers of potatoes, onion and soup mixture.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: diabetic fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in top of a double boiler over boiling water. Add evaporated milk and mix.
Cook for 3 minutes, then add vanilla and sweetener.
Spread in a small pan, chill and cut into 8 pieces.
Form balls; roll in powdered sugar or nuts.

title: baked celery
directions: Boil celery in 1 cup water for 8 minutes.
Mix with water chestnuts, pimento and soup.
Cover with crumbs and butter.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Add nuts the last 10 minutes.

title: eggnog french toast
directions: Saute apples in sugar using vegetable spray.
Continue cooking until soft.
Dip bread in eggnog coating all sides.
Cook on griddle until brown.
Serve Eggnog French Toast with apples as topping.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cheese-sausage bake(breakfast or brunch dish)
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay bread flat on bottom of pan or baking dish.
Spread grated cheese over bread.
Lay sausage pieces or slices over cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and dry mustard and pour over bread and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, then add coconut, pecans, Cool Whip and cinnamon.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: strawberry cheesecake pie
directions: Make pie shell; bake.
Beat vanilla, cream cheese and confectioners sugar until blended.
Whip the heavy cream, blend with cream cheese mixture and pour into shell.

title: no-bake yummy bars
directions: Melt chocolate morsels in microwave-safe bowl or large measuring cup on High (100%) power for 1 minute.
Stir and heat another 30 seconds or until chocolate is melted and smooth.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Cream butter until almost whipped cream like.
Cream in sugar until very light and blend in flour.
(You may need to use your hands.)
Turn onto a lightly floured board or counter and knead until very smooth and will break slightly when you push your thumb from center to edge of dough.
Divide into 4 or 5 balls (depends on preferred thickness) and press evenly into pie pans or cake pans.
Flute edges like pie crust; divide into eighths with knife, prick all over with fork.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 275° to 300° until pale brown on edges.
Cool slightly, redivide into eights, remove and cool on racks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Beat eggs and add all other ingredients with eggs.
Blend with broccoli.
Pour into a well-buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cracker crumbs (I use Ritz).
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mozzarella cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Best flavor when prepared the day before serving.
Serve with your favorite chips.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir.
Add strawberries, bananas and drained pineapple.
Set in dish.
Spread topping on after set.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Mix Jell-O with hot water until dissolved.
Add strawberry pop.
Let cool.
Punch holes in cake.
Put cake in refrigerator overnight.

title: squash relish
directions: Grind squash.
Mix squash, onions and bell peppers and bring to a boil.
Heat squash in the sugar, celery salt, vinegar, cloves and turmeric and pack in jars and seal.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, marshmallows, celery and nuts.
Add enough salad dressing to moisten. Toss lightly.
Chill.
Add additional salad dressing and garnish with red apple slices, before serving, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: summer cottage fruit salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine cottage cheese and yogurt.
Stir in pecans.
Arrange fruit on 6 lettuce lined plates.
Spoon 1/2 cup cottage cheese mixture over each.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar while hot.
Mix cranberries, orange, pineapple and nuts.
Add Jell-O mixture. Pour into mold.
Let congeal in refrigerator.

title: baked cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray Pam on a glass casserole dish. Wash potatoes.
Cut into bite size chunks.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with cheese, onion, butter and bacon bits.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serve topped with sour cream.

title: fermented pickles
directions: Pack washed cucumbers into jars with a sprig of dill, several garlic buds and as many hot peppers as you wish.
Mix the water, vinegar, canning salt and sugar.
Boil and pour over cucumbers and let set.
When cucumbers have changed color, chill and enjoy.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: In large skillet, cook onion in hot oil until almost tender. Add meat and garlic; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until sauce is thick.

title: roast beef hash
directions: Cut up leftover beef and make hash browns out of regular potatoes.
Chop onion; cook until potatoes are cooked.
Can be cooked in a frypan or boiled in a saucepan.

title: meatless moussaka(yields about 8 servings)
directions: Brush eggplant slices with oil; brown quickly on both sides. Preheat oven to 375°.
Using a very large casserole dish, layer the moussaka as follows:
tomato sauce, Parmesan cheese, eggplant slices, filling, Parmesan, eggplant, Parmesan, sauce and Parmesan on top.
Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes or until dish is hot and bubbling.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before cutting into servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour angel food cake pan. Cream margarine with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Add vanilla wafers in 4 batches alternately with milk.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 60 minutes until golden brown and tester comes out clean.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
In large frying pan, heat oil and butter over medium heat.
Add garlic cloves and cook 2 minutes without browning.
Add chicken and cook, turning until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with rosemary; add wine and chicken broth.
Cover and cook over low heat, turning once, 30 minutes or until tender.
Mix small amount of cornstarch with cold water.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Add cornstarch mixture and stir continuously over heat until gravy thickens. Return chicken to gravy and serve hot.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add salt.
Combine milk and soup.
Mix slowly into pan.
Add potatoes and onion.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss lightly to combine celery, chicken, grapes, pecans and coconut. Gradually blend into whipped cream, mayonnaise, salt and white pepper. Pour whipped cream mixture over salad ingredients; mix lightly. Cover and chill. Serve on chilled, crisp lettuce or fresh pineapple

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Wrap bacon strips around pineapple or water chestnuts.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Drain excess fat.
Mix catsup with sugar. Pour over roll-ups.
Heat until hot.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients with pastry blender; cut in butter (will look like coarse crumbs).
Mix egg and milk, then add to dough.
Stir until forms soft dough.
Knead until leaves sides of bowl.
Turn dough on floured surface; knead 12 times.
Pat in 8-inch round cake pan.
Bake at 450° for 18 minutes.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar and milk.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and cook until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool. Add confectioners sugar and beat until consistency to spread.

title: cottage noodle casserole
directions: Boil salted water and add noodles.
Continue boiling, stirring occasionally until tender.
Drain.
Combine soup mix, butter, pepper, mustard and milk in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sauce thickens.
Toss noodles with sauce, cottage cheese, applesauce, raisins and 1/2 cup cheese.
Put into 2 1/2-quart baking dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly hot.
Serves 6.

title: baked acorn squash(microwave)
directions: With a fork or small paring knife, pierce squash in several places to its center. Place squash on paper towel or plate in microwave oven. Cook on full power 10 minutes or until squash is soft; turn squash over one time while cooking. Let stand 5 minutes. Cut squash in half lengthwise; remove seeds. Place 1 teaspoon margarine and brown sugar in each half, spreading evenly. Place applesauce in each squash cavity and sprinkle cinnamon over all. Reheat 1 or 2 minutes, if desired. Makes 2 servings.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350° for crust.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Press onto bottom and 1-inch up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan or onto bottom only of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix and roll between wax paper or can pat in pan.
Makes 1 crust.

title: spinach-n-bacon salad
directions: Heat turkey bacon and onion in skillet.
Stir in spinach; cook until moist, yet firm.
Stir in potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheeses just before serving.
Makes 2 servings.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into well-greased baking dish. Top with 2 sticks butter and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: golden ham casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and celery in a small amount of boiling unsalted water until crisp-tender; drain and set aside.
Saute ham, green pepper and onion in 3 tablespoons of margarine in a medium skillet until ham is golden brown.
Place ham mixture and reserved cooked vegetables in a deep, buttered 2-quart casserole.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually stir in milk; cook until thickened.
Add cheese and salt; cook over low heat until cheese melts and mixture is slightly thickened.
Pour cheese sauce over ham and vegetables; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Melt caramels in 1/2 cup evaporated milk in saucepan over low heat; mix well.
Mix cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Add nuts.
Press half the chocolate mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: icing
directions: Cook flour, salt and milk in saucepan until thick.
Set aside and let cool.
While cooling mix together with mixer, Crisco, vanilla, and sugar.
Add cooked mixture and beat until fluffy.

title: strawberry limeade
directions: Process strawberries and lime juice in blender or food processor until smooth. Combine strawberry mixture, water and Equal in pitcher. Pour over ice cubes in tall glasses; garnish each with lime wedge or strawberry, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: "talk dirty in hawaiian" bread
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Stir in pecans.
Blend bananas, egg, pineapple and oil together.
Add this mixture to flour mixture.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: spiced grape salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups liquid using juice from your crushed pineapple and spiced grapes to make 3 cups.
Add water if not enough.
When it starts to set, add nuts, grapes and pineapple.

title: sparkling cola salad
directions: Soften cream cheese by beating either with a mixer or with a spoon.
Heat juice that was drained from pineapple and cherries. Pour over gelatin, stirring until dissolved and let cool.

title: shieldnight surprise
directions: * Sometimes I use Salsa Verde, the green kind.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; drain off excess fat.
Add next 3 ingredients; simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles in a large amount of salted boiling water until tender, drain and rinse.

title: indiana sugar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Roll pie dough out on a floured surface and use to line a 9-inch pie pan; set aside.

title: salmon soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add milk and salmon.
May thicken if you want with cornstarch.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Combine sugar, milk, eggs and margarine.
Add cocoa and flour; mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into half baked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion.
Add all ingredients except tomatoes.
Put all tomatoes in blender; blend and add to other mixture.
Simmer 3 hours.
Good with cornbread!

title: zucchini italian
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, saute beef and onion. Drain off any fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings. Simmer uncovered for 15 minutes or more, stirring occasionally. Slice zucchini lengthwise about 1/4-inch thick.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish and arrange 1/2 the slices on bottom. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Blend Ricotta, cottage cheese and eggs.
Spread over zucchini.
Top with 1/2 the Mozzarella and 1/2 meat sauce.
Layer with remaining zucchini, Mozzarella and sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan and bake, uncovered, 40 to 50 minutes or until zucchini is tender and ingredients are hot and bubbly.
Let stand for a few minutes before cutting.
Serves 8.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Bring water to boil, add grits and cook 15 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with additional cheese and red pepper.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese and red pepper on top.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Combine in pan, sugar, water and cinnamon.
Bring to hard ball candy stage.
Add pecans.
Turn off heat.
Mix so that all are coated.
Spread on cookie sheet to cool.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown ground meat; season to taste. Drain grease.
Add next 3 ingredients to meat.
Cook until heated through.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer tortillas, then meat mixture, then cheese.
Repeat layer again with flour tortillas on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, uncovered.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Put bread on bottom of oblong casserole dish.
Layer sausage and cheese over bread.
Mix eggs with other ingredients and pour on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes a wonderful breakfast for company.

title: canned homemade vegetable soup
directions: Use any other vegetables you may have on hand.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the peanut butter and cheese.
Add confectioners sugar, then fold in Cool Whip, leaving about 1/3 to spread on top.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Mix pudding and chill until set.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil in a saucepan.
Reduce heat; quickly stir in flour (use a wooden spoon for mixing).
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs all at once until smooth.
Spread into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Then lower heat to bake at 350° for an additional 20 minutes.
Cool and fill with pudding. Add Cool Whip and swirl with chocolate pudding on top.

title: venison pot roast
directions: Soak the venison roast in cold, salted water for several hours or overnight.
Drain and season with pepper and salt.
Dredge with flour and brown on all sides in hot fat in a Dutch oven.
Add the onions and water to cover.
Simmer until tender.
Potatoes and carrots may be added about 20 minutes before the roast is done.

title: butter pecan bars
directions: Beat flour, 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1/3 cup butter for 2 to 3 minutes at medium speed of mixer until particles are fine.
Pat firmly into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with pecans and press lightly.
Heat remaining 1/2 cup brown sugar and 2/3 cup butter until mixture boils.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly; drizzle over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until caramel layer is bubbly.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with chocolate chips. Let stand 2 minutes; using knife lightly swirl melted chips into caramel.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Season round steak lightly with garlic salt, salt and pepper. Cut into serving pieces and place in pot with sliced onion which has been separated into rings.
Add potatoes and green beans.
Top with tomato soup and tomatoes.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour, then turn to low for 8 hours in crock-pot or in oven for 2 hours at 375°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken.
Mix soups, water, rice and carrots.
Place soup mixture to cover the bottom of a baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Mix some of soup mixture over top.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours, or until done.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Put ingredients in a heavy Ziploc bag.
Shake to coat well. Refrigerate for 24 hours if possible, turning the bag several times.
When coals are ready, place chicken on the grill, skin side up, basting with marinade.
Cook until well brown before turning.
(If baking in oven, bake at 400°, skin side down first.) About 20 minutes before chicken is done, begin using your favorite bottled barbecue sauce.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain and set aside.
Add soup mix and rice to boiling water.
Cover and cook 7 to 8 minutes.
Then combine with all other ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(May be prepared a day before needed.)
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: salmon dinner
directions: Make macaroni and cheese dinner as directed.
Stir in soup and milk.
Gently stir in salmon and peas.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: graham cracker "heath bar" cookies
directions: Line ungreased cookie sheets with 72 graham crackers.
Bring butter, oleo and sugar to boil and continue boiling for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers, spreading "glaze" evenly over crackers.
(Continue stirring mixture in pan while pouring, while avoiding drafts.)
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 7 minutes.
Remove to wax paper immediately. When cooled, best stored in tight can.

title: canned dill relish
directions: String and prepare green beans. Put into quart jars. Add water up to the shoulders of the jar. Add 1 teaspoon canning salt and 1 teaspoon sugar. Process in pressure canner for 20 minutes at 10 pounds pressure. After I canned green beans using salt and sugar both, I found out they smell better when you open the can. Therefore, we eat them better.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, flour, salt, milk, lemon peel and juice.
In another bowl, with clean beaters, beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold into first mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 45 minutes longer or until top is golden and knife inserted in the top comes out clean. (This pie has a mild lemon flavor.)

title: jo ann's pork chop casserole
directions: Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: choc-peanut butter squares
directions: Melt butter.
Add graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Mix until smooth.
Press onto jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch).
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut at room temperature.

title: kraut salon
directions: Cook vinegar and sugar 1 minute.
When starting to boil, pour over other ingredients.
Let set 12 hours or overnight.

title: santa claus cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Add vanilla.
Add to creamed mixture.
Sift flour in slowly.
Add salt.
Chill dough for 1/2 hour.
Roll to 1/8-inch thick; cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: i can't believe i did it pie crust
directions: With a work, stir together a paste of 1/2 cup plus 2 tablespoons water with 1/2 cup flour; set aside.
Cut 1 1/2 cups shortening into 2 cups flour and salt until crumbly.
Add paste mixture; mix well.
Roll out with plenty of flour.
Makes 3 1/2 shells or 2 bottoms and 1 top.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Put all of the ingredients except nuts in a blender and blend well, then fold in nuts.
Pour into a loaf pan and bake for 60 to 65 minutes at 350°.
Serve it with love.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir onions in margarine. Stir in baking mix, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat until bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in milk gradually.
Add sour cream, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in plain or spinach egg noodles, if desired.
Makes 10 servings.

title: first class pasta sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic in large saucepan. Drain fat.
Cut up tomatoes; add tomatoes and juice, tomato paste, water, mushrooms, bay leaf, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over cooked pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna-rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, tuna and soup together.
Add grated cheese to mixture and on top, as desired.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese melts.

title: tuna quiche
directions: Puncture holes in crust before baking.
Mix tuna, cheese, onion and mushrooms.
Pour into pie crust.
Beat eggs and milk. Pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, the sour cream, pepper, pimientos and 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Pour into a shallow 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, att 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done. Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions in diagonal rows across top; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: pasta mad platter
directions: Saute onion in olive oil until soft.
Add mushrooms and continue sauteing until mushrooms change color.
All at once, add artichoke hearts, tomatoes, sausage, garlic and oregano.
Saute until warmed through but not dry.
(Can be prepared ahead to this point.)
Add spinach and saute until wilted.
Reheat pasta by immersing in hot water and draining well.
Top with spinach mixture and garnish with cheese.

title: graham cracker delights
directions: Mix together 2 sticks butter, 1 cup sugar.
Add; 1 egg beaten with 1/2 cup milk.
Bring to a boil for 2 or 3 minutes, remove from heat and stir in; graham crackers, nuts, vanilla and coconut. Place layer of whole graham crackers on a cookie sheet.
Spread on the filling; cover with another layer of crackers and smooth on the icing.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream
the
sugar, butter and shortening.
Beat in eggs one at a time.	Slowly blend in flour and baking powder.
Mix in milk,
extracts
and flavoring.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Glaze while warm.

title: ground beef tortilla casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Line dish with tortillas. Layer meat and onions, beans, cheese and more tortillas.
Spread soup on top of tortillas.
Spread Ro-Tel tomatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: instant mocha drink
directions: In a large bowl, combine creamer, cocoa, sugar, coffee, cocoa and salt.
Mix well.
Store tightly covered.
To serve, put 3 tablespoons of mix in mug.
Fill with boiling water.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Sprinkle taco seasoning over hamburger.
Add 1 cup water and stir.
Let simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat and let cool.
In large bowl, mix together the lettuce, tomato and cheese and crunch up tortilla chips in mix. Add cooled hamburger mix.
Mix in Western French dressing as needed.
Sour cream may be spooned on individual servings as desired.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together until dough is stiff (add flour if needed to make stiff).
Roll into small balls.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, cheese and onions.
Make dressing.

title: indian coleslaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over combined veggies and toss lightly.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Chop onion, pepper and celery fine.
Add to sauerkraut. Pour sugar, salad
oil
and
vinegar
over sauerkraut mixture. Will keep for weeks in refrigerator.

title: pineapple and sweet potato
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Drain pineapple and set aside.
Place sweet potatoes in 3-quart saucepan; add water.
Cook over medium heat 45 minutes.
Remove from heat and peel potatoes under cold running water.
Place in a large bowl.
Mash potatoes.
Add butter, brown sugar and pineapple.
Stir well.
Grease 1-quart casserole dish well with butter.
Spoon mixture into prepared dish.
Place marshmallows on top of mixture and bake, uncovered, for about 30 minutes.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water, cornstarch, butter and salt in 2-quart pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring with a wooden spoon until 256°.
Stir in vanilla and pour into buttered 8-inch pan. When cool, pull until light in color and stiff.
Cut into small pieces and wrap in waxed paper.

title: three hundred dollar cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together; stir well and set aside. Place margarine, cocoa, water and oil together in saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour over flour mixture, mixing well. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla; mix completely. The batter will be thin. Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: raspberry sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Cook until thickened and remove from heat.
Add 1 wooden spoonful of lemon juice and stir.
Allow to sit for flavors to blend, but reheat before serving.
Good over peaches and ice cream.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown together the ground beef and sausage and drain.
Combine with other ingredients; spread on rye bread (party size).
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: deviled ham cheese ball
directions: Blend together all ingredients and form into a ball.
Chill several hours.
(Can be rolled in nuts, if desired.)

title: date nut cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 275° for 2 hours.
