title: pot roast chuck
directions: Place beef on heavy-duty foil in pan.

title: cheese grits(from the files of louella scott williams)
directions: Pour grits slowly in 2 1/2 cups boiling water and maintain low boil until dry, stirring regularly, about 8 minutes.
(Will make about 2 1/2 cups grits; for other type grits, follow directions on box to get equivalent amount.)
While warm, add margarine, cheese, seasoned salt and Tabasco sauce and mix well.
Allow to cool.
Beat eggs really well and add to grits mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased, buttered deep baking dish.
Slow cook at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Pour into greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: candy box parfaits
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; mix cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into jello until slightly thickened. Remove any remaining ice cubes.
Stir in strawberries.
Divide into 6 dessert dishes.
Refrigerate until just set, about 10 minutes (not firm).
Pour milk into bowl and pudding mix.
Beat with whisk for 2 minutes.
Spoon about 1/4 cup pudding into each dish.
Chill 1 hour or until set.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter and combine rest of ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: plain doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Stir in butter.
Add sifted dry ingredients with milk.
Add 2 to 4 tablespoons flour, if necessary to make a soft dough.
Roll on floured surface to 3/4-inch thickness and cut with donut cutter.
Fry in hot (hot, not smoking) oil for about 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Roll in powdered sugar, sugar or cinnamon-sugar.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix: sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake in 4 (1 pound) coffee cans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: to clean tupperware
directions: *BLKLIN coat with cocoa instead of flour.
The sides will be more attractive.

title: "mama smith's" cheese and macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Drain almost dry.
Add cheese and mix.
Mix butter with cheese and macaroni.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in mayonnaise and milk.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 500° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom with 8 slices torn bread.
Cook and drain loose sausage.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Sprinkle on shredded cheese next.
Whip eggs with 2 cups milk.
Pour over top; it will sink into bread.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: In bowl, combine rice, cooked noodles, 1/4 cup egg substitute and half the cheese.
Mix well.
Pat into bottom and up the sides of a 9-inch pie plate coated with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In another bowl, combine broccoli, mushrooms, milk, oil and remaining egg substitute.
Pour into crust.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Cream first six ingredients together.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal and Rice Krispies. Refrigerate overnight.
Using 1 teaspoon of batter, form into balls.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix sugar and Miracle Whip.
Add water, baking soda, salt, vanilla and cocoa; mix well.
Add flour to mixture and beat. Grease and flour an oblong pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: okra salad
directions: Fry okra.
Salt and pepper to taste.
When brown, drain oil. Mix with chopped vegetables.
Cover and shake.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: coconut fruit bowl
directions: Combine fruits, marshmallows and coconut.
Stir in sour cream and salt.
Chill overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together well.
Set several hours or overnight.
Add 2 sliced bananas before serving.

title: fudge no bake cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in saucepan; bring to boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.
Let cool.

title: pressed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until very tender.
Remove bones and cut meat very fine.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
To hot broth add crackers and butter.
Add chicken and mix well.
Add a bit more broth if needed.
Put in a loaf pan; press with weight and let cool.
Slice and serve.

title: mexican cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back in the middle.

title: green rice
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine until soft.
Add slightly thawed broccoli and heat.
Add cheese and soup to rice.
Mix well.
Mix all together, then pour into buttered casserole dish.
Put grated cheese on top and heat in hot oven until cheese is bubbly on top, about 15 minutes.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers, carrots and onions thin.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly.
Chill 8 to 10 hours, tossing lightly once.
Drain and serve.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Mix oranges, coconut, marshmallows and pineapple.
Moisten with sour cream and chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chew bread
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Beat well.
Then add coconut and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: sausage hash brown casserole
directions: Cook the sausage until browned;

drain well. In a large mixing bowl, combine the cheese, chicken soup, sour cream, French onion dip, chopped onion, chopped pepper, salt and pepper to taste. Fold in thawed hash brown potatoes; mix well. Spread 1/2 the hash brown mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish. Spread half the browned sausage over the hash browns. Repeat layering hash browns, ending with sausage on top. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: raisin oat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line muffin pan cups with paper baking cups or spray with vegetable cooking spray.

Set aside. In medium bowl, pour buttermilk over oats. In a small bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. Add mixture to soaked oats. In a small bowl, combine egg substitute, brown sugar, oil and maple flavoring.
Pour into flour mixture. Add raisins. Gently fold together until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy. Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted into center of a muffin comes out clean.
Remove from pan. Cool 5 minutes and serve. Makes 12 large muffins.

title: spiced apple loaf
directions: Blend butter with sugar and beat well until smooth and creamy. Add eggs and continue to beat until blended.
Add flour, salt, spices, baking powder, lemon rind and nuts.
Sprinkle the apple cubes with flour and cinnamon sugar.
Fold gently into batter. Pour batter into a loaf pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the loaf tests done.

title: apricot angel brownies
directions: If you are tired of chocolate brownies, please try these.
In saucepan, melt white chunks and butter, stirring constantly until everything is melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Set aside.

title: potato casserole
directions: Allow potatoes to defrost (at least partially).
Mix all together.
Place in large greased casserole.
Bake about 45 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Heat broth to boiling.
Reduce heat; stir in chicken and vegetables.
Mix flour and water to make a smooth sauce.
Pour into meat and vegetable mixture slowly and stir constantly until thickened.

title: shrimp deluxe
directions: Make sauce of first 5 ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and ready to boil.
Carefully add next ingredients, one at a time, stirring and blending well.
Flavor improves if made a day ahead.
Serve over rice.
Cook shrimp until they turn pink, it doesn't take long.

title: fresh plum pie
directions: Quarter and pit plums.
Should have 1-quart.

In a large saucepan, thoroughly stir together sugar, cornstarch, salt and ginger; add plums, margarine, orange rind and orange juice. Stirring constantly over medium heat, cook until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Cool slightly. Pour filling into pastry lined pie plate.
Top with remaining pastry. Seal edges.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: dirt
directions: Grind
up
Oreos
until they look like dirt; set aside. Blend cream cheese, milk and pudding.
Fold in whipping cream. Alternate pudding
and Oreos in a flower pot.
End with Oreos and add gummy worms.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, beating until well mixed. Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Fold in sweet potatoes, persimmons, coconut and raisins.
Add vanilla. Bake in two 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pans at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in salt, extract, flour and pecans.
Mix well.
Chill several hours.
Shape dough into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 300° to 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
When completely cooled, roll in confectioners sugar again.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients with ground beef and simmer over low heat for approximately 15-30 minutes.

title: chicken and dumpling stew
directions: Chop vegetables into chunks.
Melt butter in a Dutch oven; add chicken and vegetables.
Cook until chicken is lightly browned and vegetables are crisp-tender.
Sprinkle with flour and spices. Cook about 2 minutes until all are coated.
Gradually add broth; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low and simmer.
While chicken simmers, prepare dumplings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Melt shortening in hot water (not boiling).
Mix sugar, eggs and salt together; add this to shortening and water mixture.
Add 2 to 3 cups flour.
Sprinkle yeast onto flour and mix well.
Add remaining flour and mix.
Turn out onto floured board and knead about 10 minutes.
Place dough in large, lightly greased bowl and turn over.

title: egg strata
directions: Trim and cube bread in 1-inch pieces. Cut cheese into chunks. Layer bread on bottom with cheese on top of bread in an 8 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Next, mix rest of ingredients and pour on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: creamy italian
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container; cover.
Blend on medium speed 15 seconds or until smooth.
Cover.
Chill.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: avocado-shrimp wraps
directions: In covered jar shake together oil, vinegar, juice, cilantro, zest, ginger, sugar, garlic, salt and pepper until salt dissolves. In plastic food storage bag mix 1/2 cup of mixture with shrimp; refrigerate 1 hour.
Refrigerate remaining oil mixture.
Drain shrimp, discarding marinade.
In nonstick skillet over medium heat cook shrimp, turning once, until pink and opaque, 3 minutes per side.
With slotted spoon remove shrimp from skillet; discard pan juices.
To assemble, arrange tortillas on work surface; layer shrimp, avocado, radishes and sprouts in line up center of top two thirds of each tortilla.
Fold bottom third of tortilla over filling; fold sides over filling.
Wrap tightly in plastic until ready to serve.
Just before serving drizzle remaining oil mixture over filling of each tortilla.

title: sicilian chicken (cous' recipe)*
directions: Saute some onion in olive oil.
Add chicken, cut into pieces. Add vinegar peppers.
Saute briefly.
Remove from heat.
Drain all liquid from the pan.
Add olives.
Add some juice from vinegar peppers, about 1 tablespoon.
Add capers, salt, black pepper, paprika, oregano, garlic and mushrooms.
Return to heat.
Add butter. Let it melt through the mixture.
Any of these quantities or ingredients may be varied.

title: easy no rise yeast rolls
directions: Mix ingredients except flour.
Add enough self-rising flour to make dough of right consistency.
Cut out and bake at 400° until done.
Before browning, put butter on top.
Dough will keep up to a week, covered, in the refrigerator.

title: lemon dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping as directed on package, using 1 cup milk in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining milk to pudding mix. Whip them at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Spoon into baked pie shell or cracker crumb crust.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving.

title: bacon rolls(appetizers)
directions: Spread cream cheese on bread slice.
Cut into thirds and roll each piece in bacon slice.
Secure with toothpicks.
Freeze.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend all of the ingredients (except broccoli), then fold in broccoli.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle additional dressing mix on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and raisins. Roll in balls about the size of a walnut. Place on cookie sheet and flatten with fork. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn hot in oven (300° to 350°).
Butter sides of saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook to hard ball stage (250°).
Pour slowly over popcorn; mix well to coat all kernels. Make balls (press) using shortening or butter to keep from sticking to hands.

title: chili
directions: Cook hamburger and drain off grease.
Add onion to meat and cook until done.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer about 30 to 40 minutes until cooked to desired thickness.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix together and shape into balls.
Place in glass baking dish.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes, tossed in 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: onion steak
directions: Combine flour and seasonings; pound into steak.
Cut steak into serving size pieces.
In skillet, brown steak in shortening and pour off fat.
Add soup and ketchup.
Cover; cook over low heat 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Add green pepper; cook 15 minutes more until done.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sara's favorite potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes; cut in wedges.
Put potatoes in large pot and cover with water.
Add herbs.
Cook potatoes until done (10 to 15 minutes).
Spoon 1/3 of mixture into blender and puree.
Pour back into pot.
Stir soup.
Spoon 1/3 of stirred mixture into blender and puree.
Pour back and stir.
Ladle soup into bowls; garnish with one handful cheese.
Serve.
(Serves approximately 4, depending on appetites!)

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, butter and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix well; press in bottom of paper cupcake cups.
Mix cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Place on top of crumb mixture.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
When cool, top with your favorite topping.

title: oven-fried chicken tahini(deborah morgan, albuquerque)
directions: In a large bowl, combine tahini, yogurt, lemon juice, garlic and parsley.
In another bowl, mix stuffing with sesame seed. Coat chicken pieces with tahini mixture.
Lift out and lay meatiest side in stuffing mix.

Place pieces, crumbs up, in a single layer in a 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake in a 375° oven until meat at thigh bone is no longer pink (cut to test), about 45 minutes. Accompany with lemon wedges, salt and pepper to add to taste.
Serves 4.

title: cheesy crab dip
directions: Mix and spread first 4 ingredients into a shallow appetizer dish.
Sprinkle cheese over.
Microwave for 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with Nabisco Waverly crackers.

title: reita's surprise pie
directions: Mix together milk and lemon juice. Refrigerate until cool. Drain pineapple thoroughly. Add to juice mixture.
Stir in pecans. Fold in Cool Whip and blend thoroughly.
Pour into pie crusts and chill at least 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat egg whites separately and fold in last.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then turn oven to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Blend all together. Add pecans on top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and cook the cranberries in 1 cup of water until done. Mix jello in hot water.
Cool and add other ingredients.
Congeal.

title: sauteed shrimp
directions: In a saute pan or skillet over medium heat, heat oil with basil; add shallot.
Saute until tender; do not brown.
Add shrimp and cook, stirring 3 to 5 minutes, or just until pink.
Squeeze lemon onto shrimp; season to taste and sprinkle with parsley. Serve from pan at table.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together first 4
ingredients
with
a
fork.
In a separate dish, beat
remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients until well mixed.
Using your hands, mold into 4 balls. Chill at least 15
minutes
before
using,
or
you may freeze until ready to use.

title: corn casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine everything and bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: spicy almond chicken
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook about 10 minutes or until brown.
Place chicken in a Pam-sprayed 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Mix Jiffy mix according to directions.
Brown meat and onion in 1 tablespoon shortening.
Add seasonings and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.
Add 1 can dark red kidney beans.
Pour meat mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with corn bread batter.
Spread with wet knife.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: ragalach
directions: Mix butter, cream cheese and salt until creamy.
Mix in flour. Shape into 14 balls.
Refrigerate overnight.
Heat oven to 350°. On lightly floured surface, roll each ball to a 6-inch circle. Cut each into quarters.
Mix nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto each quarter.
Pinch together edges of dough, then form into crescents.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes, until light brown.
Best served fresh.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Cook hamburger, green pepper and onion in skillet.
Drain grease.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening at medium speed.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs and beat until very fluffy using #8 speed.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to other ingredients alternately with mashed bananas, combined buttermilk and vanilla at #1 speed, scraping sides and bottom of bowl frequently during mixing.
When thoroughly blended, pour into 2 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until cake tests done.

title: fresh mushroom scallop
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Cover bottom of a greased, shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish with a layer of potatoes.
Sprinkle with some of the flour mixture.
Add a layer of mushrooms.
Sprinkle with some of the Parmesan cheese; dot with butter.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Pour milk over baking dish.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes. Remove cover and continue baking until potatoes are tender and top is browned, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley. Makes 6 servings.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar and slowly add the flour.
Add eggs and mix well.
Chill overnight.
Roll out thin on floured board. Cut out with round cookie cutter.
Brush with egg whites and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Press walnut halve in center of each cookie.
Bake at 350 for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate banana cake
directions: Combine all; beat 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Thoroughly combine crushed fruit and yogurt in bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Spoon into crust and freeze about 4 hours.
Remove from freezer and store in refrigerator for 30 minutes before serving.
Garnish with fresh strawberry slices.

title: incredible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate or pan (10 x 1 1/2-inches).
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion on plate or pan. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minutes with hand beater.
Pour into pan.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sourdough raisin bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, raisins and cinnamon well before adding starter, water and oil.
Mix well.
Brush with small amount of oil, cover with Saran Wrap.
Let rise until more than double in size, 6 to 12 hours.
Using flour on counter or pastry cloth, knead a minute or two until smooth.
Divide into 3 parts, put in greased loaf pans and brush lightly with oil.
Let rise 4 to 5 hours or all day.
Cover lightly with wax paper.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake on bottom of rack.
Brush with butter.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain and mix with sour cream and soup.
Cook onion and pepper with squash.
Mix 1 stick butter with stuffing.
Mix well.
Put 1/2 in casserole dish.
Put squash mixture on top of that and put the rest of the stuffing on top. Bake 30 minutes 350°.

title: shrimp hors d'ouevres
directions: Blend all ingredients (except shrimp) in blender until smooth. Add to shrimp.
Blend and marinate 24 hours in refrigerator.
May also be served as a first course.

title: corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in an oiled casserole dish for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick dessert
directions: Place whole honey graham crackers in rectangle baking dish. Slice 3 bananas on the crackers.
Beat 1 small box of vanilla instant pudding with 1 1/2 cups cold milk.
Add 1 cup topping to the pudding.
Mix well and spread over bananas.
Sprinkle coconut on top and sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Garnish with cherries, if you wish.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: macaroni and shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: easter eggs
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until you hear it crack in cold water when tested.
Add slowly to stiffly beaten egg whites and beat until mixture begins to thicken. Add fruit and nuts.
Cool slightly and form into shape using confectioners sugar to keep from sticking to the hands.
When cold, spread with melted semi-sweet chocolate.

title: blueberry pear cobbler
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch in a medium saucepan. Stir in water, bring to boil over medium heat.
Cook 1 minute. Remove from heat and gently stir in blueberries and pears.
Spoon mixture into 9-inch square baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.

title: lo-cal fruit salad
directions: Choose fruits in own juice (no sugar added).
Drain fruit and reserve pineapple juice.
Mix together pudding, Tang and reserved pineapple juice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: corn, cheese and chili pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour mixture into baking dish and bake on center rack for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until pie is firm when pressed in center.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Blend butter and peanut butter together.
Add sugar and crumbs.
Roll into small balls.
Chill while you melt the chocolate chips with paraffin wax over hot water.
With a toothpick, stick into chilled candy balls.
Dip into melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper until chilled.

title: yummy yummy omelet
directions: Cook all ingredients in skillet.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Peel and parboil potatoes.
Line (ungreased) casserole dish with half of the potatoes.
Add 4 pats of butter on top of the potatoes.
Then add sliced cheese on top of that.
Add a second layer of potatoes, butter and cheese.
Lay the pork chops on top of all this.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Fill casserole dish half full with milk.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour; mix well.
Stir in chocolate pieces and walnuts.
Press mixture into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until brown.
Cut into bars while warm.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, add sour cream last.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: cheesy garden chowder
directions: In soup kettle, saute onion in butter over medium heat until tender.
Add water, vegetables, bouillon cubes, parsley, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until veggies are tender.

title: apple pie crunch
directions: Peel and slice thinly the apples.
Put into oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup of sugar over apples.
Melt butter and add 1/2 cup of sugar to butter.
Mix in flour to make a paste.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
When cooked, bone and let cool. Flatten crescent rolls and place 1/2 slice cheese and slice of chicken breast on roll.
Roll up and place in casserole dish. (One can of rolls will make 8 roll-ups.)
Bring cream of chicken soup diluted with one can of milk to a boil.
Pour over rolls and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add seasonings; stir until blended.
Stir in bell pepper and tomatoes.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and heat.
Use flour at this stage to thicken.
Taste for additional seasonings. Serve over rice.

title: peach spice rice
directions: Add cinnamon, almonds, margarine and sugar to cooked rice.
Mix well.
Place rice mixture in peach halves and around plate.
Broil 5 minutes.
Serves 14.

title: corn
directions: Put butter in skillet; add corn, salt and pepper.
Add about 1/4 cup of water.
Boil until water is gone.

title: apple betty
directions: Pour two cans pie filling into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over the top.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Add nuts over top.
Bake in a preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mushrooms parmesan
directions: Toss mushrooms with the oil in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine dry ingredients and sprinkle over mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter in skillet.
Cook 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Set aside.

title: lena's banana pudding
directions: Mix the pie filling with 3 cups milk.
When mixed well, add the Cool Whip.
Stir until the Cool Whip and pie filling are mixed well.
Then layer in large bowl wafers, bananas and pie filling. keep doing this until you have used all of it.
Crush up 10 wafers to sprinkle over top.

title: orzo salad(yield: 12 servings)
directions: 1. Cook orzo according to directions, al dente.

title: whole beef brisket
directions: Score the meat with a knife on meat side (go with the grain of the meat).
Place meat side down in roaster.
Mix chili sauce, Coke and onion soup mix.
Pour over brisket and cook, covered, in 325° oven for 3 to 5 hours (about 30 minutes per pound or until fork tender).
When done, slice against the grain (start at tip). Refrigerate sauce; when fat comes to top, skim it off.
Heat brisket with the sauce on it at 350° for 30 minutes.
Be careful not to burn sauce.

title: brie bread
directions: Diagonally slice French bread into 1/2-inch slices not quite cutting through bottom crust. Drizzle butter over the bread and set aside.

title: hamburger helper casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Drain mixed vegetables.
Mix all together in large skillet.
Heat and stir over medium heat a few minutes.

title: apricot pie
directions: Beat 3 egg whites until very stiff. Fold a cup of strained baby apricots into them together with lemon juice and sugar.
Pour into crust. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
This dessert is low in calories and high in fiber content.

title: make ahead chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Spread evenly over bottom of large oven-proof baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Place pieces of chicken breast over top of rice.
Blend other ingredients and pour over chicken and rice, saving slivered almonds to sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, after covering with aluminum foil.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.

title: aunt sara's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and syrup; beat again.
Add melted butter, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Then lower heat to 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: continental salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin with the hot grapefruit juice.
Add 1/2 cup of beet juice.
Chill until partially thickened.
Fold in drained beets, celery and lemon juice.
Pour into mold.
Chill and serve with sesame dressing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Flour cut up chicken.
Salt and pepper.
Fry in Wesson oil until brown.
Put in casserole dish. Add other ingredients and bake until chicken is done.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat egg in a cup and fill cup with water.
Mix flour and shortening with pastry blender.
Add other ingredients.
Roll and put into pans.
This recipe makes 5 pie crusts which may be frozen with good results.

title: sour cream ginger cookies
directions: Beat together brown sugar, sour cream, molasses, egg and lemon extract.
Sift together flour, soda and ginger.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered baking sheet. Remove immediately to wire rack to cool.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: shrimp imperial
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add peppers and onions and saute. Add Ro-Tel, tomato sauce and shrimp. Add salt and pepper to taste. When shrimp are done, add Cheez Whiz. When cheese has melted, turn down heat and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Flake salmon and add eggs. Mix well. Add crumbs, salt and pepper. Mix well and form into balls the size of a tablespoon. Fry in oil in deep fat fryer until golden brown.

title: no cook diabetic cookies
directions: Cook oleo, milk and unsweetened chocolate for 1 minute, stirring while cooking.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Pat mixture out into small patties.
Place on waxed paper to cool.
Do not bake.
May be frozen.

title: portuguese roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Wash and cut meat into serving pieces. Chop onion and garlic.
Put all ingredients in roasting pan and mix together.
Bake for 1 hour.
Lower heat to 350° and continue to cook for 1 more hour, until tender.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Mix together cocoa, food coloring and vinegar; add to batter.
Add vanilla.
Make 3 layers. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: garden yogurt salad
directions: Arrange zucchini in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Add cucumber, tomato, onion and garlic.
Toss with yogurt, parsley, dill, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Top with sesame seed and sprouts.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato pancakes(kartoflane placki)
directions: Grate large potatoes and drain off excess juice.
Measure the pulp and add remaining ingredients. Beat well.
Heat 4 tablespoons shortening in a skillet. Drop in batter by tablespoonfuls. Spread thinly and fry to a deep brown on each side.
Vegetable, meat or chicken fat will give much crisper pancakes than butter.
A teaspoonful of grated onion adds flavor.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; slice into paper thin slices.
Combine cucumbers, onions, green peppers and salt.
Mix with 1 quart crushed ice and let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and bring slowly to a boiling point.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal at once.
Let stand at least 30 days before using to get best flavor.

title: grape swirl refrigerator cookies
directions: In a bowl, combine jam, nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
In a large bowl, cream butter or margarine.
Gradually stir in sugars and beat until mixture is light.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat until mixture is thoroughly blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Gradually stir into the creamed mixture; mix thoroughly.
Divide the dough in half. Roll out each half into a rectangle on a lightly floured surface, about 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread with half of the jam mixture. Roll up jellyroll fashion.
(The rolls will be about 2-inches in diameter.)
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill overnight.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices with sharp knife.
Place on greased baking sheets about 1/2-inch apart.
Bake in hot oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are light brown.
Remove from baking sheets as soon as possible as cookies are done.

title: bread pudding
directions: Add bread crumbs to hot milk; cool.
Combine sugar, eggs, margarine, salt, vanilla, raisins, nutmeg and cinnamon with bread crumb mixture.
Pour into buttered baking dish; place dish in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large bowl mix spaghetti and oil.
In a small bowl combine eggs, 1/2 cup parmesan cheese.
Stir egg/cheese mixture into the spaghetti.
Pour spaghetti mixture into a lightly grease 10 inch pie plate and form into a crust.
Spread ricotta evenly over the crust but not to the edge.
Top with the sauce.
Bake uncovered 25 minutes.
Top with the mozzarella cheese, return to oven for 5 minutes or until melted.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons of parmesan cheese.
Allow to cool for 10 minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of double boiler (not over heat).
Beat 1 minute with electric or rotary beater to blend.
Place over boiling water and cook, beating constantly until frosting forms stiff peaks, about 7 minutes (don't overcook).
Remove from boiling water.
Pour into mixing bowl, if you wish.
Add vanilla and beat until it is spreading consistency, about 2 minutes.

title: pork chops with gherkins
directions: Salt chops and let stand 10 minutes.
Melt the butter in a large saucepan.
When foaming, put chops in.
Saute chops 3 minutes on each side over a high fire.
Add the onions and cook 5 minutes on lower fire.
Drain the grease and the Madeira, demi-glace, mustard and gherkins.
Simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
Place chops on a serving platter.
Keep warm.
Add sugar and pepper to sauce and cook 5 minutes.
Pour the sauce over the chops and serve very hot.

title: garden-style tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain.
Rinse with hot water.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Cool.
Using a large punch bowl, break 1/2 of cake in
pieces into bowl and layer with 1/2 of ingredients.
Repeat layers.
Top with Cool Whip, cherries and chopped nuts.
Serves a large crowd.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash and cut up chicken.
Put cooking oil in skillet about one-inch deep on low heat.
Roll chicken in flour.
Season with salt, pepper and meat tenderizer.
Place chicken in skillet and turn occasionally until done.
Drain, then eat.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the vegetables with the cheese, sour cream and soup.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix the cracker crumbs, almonds and butter and place on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds of peppers.
Parboil 5 minutes and drain. Brown onion and meat in fat or Pam spray; add tomatoes, corn and seasonings; stuff peppers and top with bread crumbs.
Stand upright in oiled baking dish; add small amount water.
Cover and bake in 350° oven 1 hour.
Serves 8.
